title: sauteed mushrooms and onions
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onions and saute over medium heat until onions are translucent.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper. Saute until mushrooms are cooked.

title: caviar pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and add mayonnaise, onion, Worcestershire sauce and lemon.
Spread in center of plate about 1-inch thick. Sprinkle with chopped eggs, then onion and make an outer circle of parsley with caviar in center.
Serve with toast rounds.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and shape into ball.
Chill in foil overnight.
Roll in nuts of your choice.

title: grandma tom's banana bread
directions: Mix together. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: baked peaches
directions: Line peach halves in ovenproof dish or muffin tin.
Dot each peach with butter, brown sugar and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with ice cream on side.

title: squash pickles
directions: Place first four ingredients in a large pan.
Sprinkle with canning salt, no water.
Let set an hour or more.
Drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Add squash mixture and boil not less than 1 minute.
Seal in hot jars.
Makes 4 pints.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water; bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add 1 (3 ounce) package of strawberry Jell-O.
Cool and add 2 pints of fresh strawberries.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers and margarine, together and put in casserole dish.
Cover with finely crushed Ritz crackers and place pats of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until almost no imprint remains when touched.
Cool on racks.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: beverly's red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans - cover with water and start to cook at a good boil.
(You don't have to use the whole 2 lb. bag, adjust to suit taste).
Add hot sausage and chopped onion.
Break sausage apart as it starts to cook.
Cook for about 20-30 minutes then add tomatoes with juice.
Continue cooking until beans just start to soften then add Smokey Hollow Sausage sliced.
Cook about 15-20 minutes more.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: jar celery
directions: Trim leaves from celery; separate ribs from heart (should be 10 large ribs).
Wash and drain ribs.
Cut into 1/2-inch diagonal slices to make 5 cups.
In deep 10-inch skillet, mix the remaining ingredients.
Boil gently for 20 minutes.
Pour into jar.
Press down to have marinade cover celery.
Cover and chill before serving.
Serve as part of antipasta or salad or as a relish.

title: quick casserole
directions: Microwave the frozen vegetables for 8 minutes.
Mix soup and sour cream, pour over vegetables and top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sandy's chicken or turkey salad
directions: I put each ingredient separately in the food processor and chop, then mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or as a sandwich spread.

title: butter mints
directions: Cream the butter and add sugar until mixture gets stiff.
Add boiling water, one tablespoon at a time.
Add oil and food coloring. Continue adding sugar.
Mixture should be fairly stiff. Mold in candy molds or roll out and cover with melted chocolate, then cut into pieces.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken.
After done, allow to cool.
As it is cooking, cook broccoli.
Add onion and celery to chicken broth and boil. Then add soup and milk to broth mixture.
Then layer broccoli and chicken in casserole pan.
Next, layer some cheese, then add soup and broth mixture on top.
Top with crushed potato chips and more cheese.
Bake in buttered pan for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Form into patties and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until firm.
Serves 12.

title: chili con carne
directions: In heavy skillet, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is lightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.

title: colorful vegetable salad
directions: Layer half of vegetables in large salad bowl.
Repeat.
Pour Italian dressing over vegetables; cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
This will keep several days.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water until fork tender. Cool, alternate carrots, pepper rings and onions thinly sliced. Make a marinade of remaining ingredients, blending well. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until crisp, 5 minutes; drain.
Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook fryer, onion flakes and chicken bouillon cubes until chicken is tender enough to fall off bone.
Take chicken out of pot to debone.
While chicken is being deboned, cook celery and carrots in broth until tender.
Put chicken pieces and noodles in pot and cook until noodles are tender.

title: triple chocolate pie
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on package.
Set aside to cool completely. In mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until pudding is completely cool. After cooling pudding, layer over cream cheese. Spread Cool Whip over pudding and refrigerate until firm.

title: prune nut cupcakes
directions: Combine ingredients as you do in cake.
Bake in small cupcake pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: baked apple dumplings
directions: Roll each biscuit to about a 5-inch diameter; fill with 1/3 to 1/2 cup diced apples.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon; top with a pat of margarine.
Fold half of biscuit over and close with tines of fork; prick top of each pie (or dumpling).
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: rice pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook!

title: baked country ham
directions: Soak ham in cold water, changing water twice in 24 hours. Scrub ham and trim fat.
Place in baking dish and pour ginger ale over ham until you have approximately 1-inch in pan.
Pour 2 quarts apple juice over ham and baste with brown sugar.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 450° and then turn oven to 375° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: mrs. jones meat loaf
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper until soft.
Mix eggs, ketchup, thyme and oatmeal together with meat.
Make sure oatmeal can be seen.
Then mix onion, celery and peppers together with meat mixture.

title: fish cakes
directions: Combine fish, onion, lemon juice, seasonings, egg and potatoes.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into cakes.
Coat cakes with flour and saute in hot fat/oil until brown on both sides.

title: 8 layer salad
directions: Keep ingredients in layers as listed.
When serving, be sure to get all layers.

title: bahama bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
Cream the butter in a mixing bowl.
Gradually add the sugar and mix until well blended.
Add the eggs and bananas; mix until well blended.
Combine the milk and lemon juice in a large bowl. Alternately mix the flour mixture into the banana.
Add a little at a time, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
Add nuts.
Turn the batter into a heavily buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until bread is golden and springs back when touched.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Take bread out of pan and cool completely.

title: my buns
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in 1 cup water. Heat and melt Crisco. Add other 2 cups water. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Put 9 cups of flour in big bowl and make a hole in center and put in water; mix well. Put last cup flour on table and knead dough well until no longer sticky. Put back in bowl and cover. Let rise until doubled. Make into buns and let rise until doubled again. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: aioli with fall vegetables(serves 4)
directions: Prepare sauce by mixing yogurt, mayonnaise and garlic in serving bowl.
Keep at room temperature while vegies cook.
Use large steamer for vegies.
Cut potatoes into chunks.
They take about 20 minutes to cook.
Cut other vegies into chunks and add at appropriate times.
Allow at least 10 minutes for all vegetables. Add onion, cut in large crescents, on top.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix and heat to boiling pineapple, flour and sugar.
Add jello and cool 10 minutes.
Add cherries, bananas and nuts.
Pour into cooled pie shells and top with Cool Whip.
Chill.
Makes 2 large or 3 regular pies.

title: "n b c" soup(noodles, broccoli, cheese)
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Add bouillon cubes and noodles.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add broccoli, salt and garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes, then add milk and cheese, simmering for 1 hour.
Stir often.

title: cream corn and crawfish soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until tender. Add crawfish tails and saute for 2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except half and half.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Add half and half and heat without letting it come to a boil.
Easy and tasty.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix together buttermilk, Wesson oil and sugar.
Dissolve yeast in water and mix with buttermilk mixture.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Then add to liquid, a little at a time.
Mix well.
Store covered in refrigerator.
You do not have to let rise before baking.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: best baked custard
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Gradually stir in milk.
Pour into six 6 ounce custard cups. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place cups in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; pour very hot water into pan to within 1/2 inch of tops of cups. Bake for 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Remove cups from water.
Serve custard warm or chilled.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra in pint jars.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over okra in jars and seal right away.
Should be ready to eat in about 3 to 4 weeks.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: Brown beef and onion in large skillet on medium heat.
Drain. Stir in water, ketchup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil. Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand 3 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: hacienda dip(microwave)
directions: Mix cream cheese, salsa and salt until well blended.
Spread cheese mixture in microwavable pie plate or bowl.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring every 2 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Cooking time:
4 minutes.

title: herb-roasted potatoes
directions: Toss together all ingredients in a large bowl.	Spread mixture evenly into a lightly greased, aluminum foil-lined 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until tender.	Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican beans
directions: Boil beans until halfway cooked.
Add fried bacon, diced onions, tomatoes, olives and juice and cilantro.
Cook slowly until done.

title: cactus salad
directions: Cook rice and chicken separately.
Mix together with other ingredients and cook until done.

title: evan's mexican layered surprise(yield: 4-6 servings)
directions: 1. Dice onions and tomatoes, add salt and mix together.
Set aside.

title: no heat pickles
directions: Soak whole cucumbers in salt water 1 week.
Wash cucumbers and slice thin.
Soak in alum for 24 hours.
Rinse well.
Cover with vinegar and let stand 24 hours.
Pour off vinegar.
Layer cucumbers with sugar and spices (mixed pickling spice and cloves). More than 5 pounds of sugar may be used.
These pickles do not have to be sealed.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in oiled dish. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Crush 2 cups corn flakes.
Put on top.
Pour 1/4 cup margarine over top after it has baked 1 hour. Use 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: fresh gooseberry pie
directions: Measure 1/2 cup berries and mash.
Mix together the sugar and cornstarch and stir into mashed berries.
Cook until clear and bubbling, about 1 minute.
It will be thick.
Allow to cool and add to remaining 2 1/2 cups of whole berries.
Put into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and beef casserole(low-fat)
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish with cooking spray. Cut dried beef into strips and put onto bottom of dish. Add chicken breasts. Mix soup and sour cream. Spoon on top of chicken. Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: mom's biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients; then add almost 1 cup milk.
Mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Delicious served with chicken and gravy or pork and gravy.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 2 tablespoons cocoa, milk, oil and vanilla together in a bowl.
Pour into an ungreased square pan, along with the flour and sugar.
Mix with a fork until smooth. Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with light brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: "supper" spinach
directions: Season spinach to taste and simmer.
Slice onions very thin and place on large platter.
Pour hot spinach over onions and top with sliced eggs.
Serve with hot corn bread and smoked sausage. So good!

title: harvest apple salad
directions: Core and cube apples. Peel banana; cut lengthwise and then cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Blend apples, bananas and yogurt. Keep refrigerated until serving.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine ingredients except coconut and pecans.
Cook over medium heat, 10 to 12 minutes,
stirring
constantly.
Remove from
heat; add remaining ingredients.
Beat until
cool
and of spreading consistency. Good with chocolate cake.

title: twenty-four hour layered salad
directions: Layer 2/3 of lettuce, all the peas, cheese, onion, celery and remaining lettuce in small glass bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill for at least 6 hours to overnight.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Top with bacon and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding, milk, powdered sugar, vanilla and Cool Whip. Layer graham crackers and mix.
Cover with chocolate frosting. Chill.

title: corn custard
directions: Put eggs, flour, sugar, milk and salt into blender.
Blend well.
Add corn and blend again.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: glorified rice
directions: Use 2 cups hot water for mixing jello.
Add sugar to whipping cream.
Fold the jello, pineapple, nuts and rice into whipping cream after the jello has chilled.
Whip the jello enough to be frothy before folding in other ingredients.
Pour into a long shallow pan for chilling, 3 to 4 hours.

title: creamy-rich peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar with milk (half and half); stir well.
Then let set for 2 hours until all dissolved.
Boil until mixture forms solid ball in water.
(Important, do not stir while cooking.)
Let set until lukewarm.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until like heavy fudge.
Knead in a clean, damp cloth until creamy.
Roll into long sheet.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll into jelly roll and slice into pieces.

title: chicken or steak shish kabobs
directions: Cut chicken breasts or steaks into 1 to 1 1/2-inch cubes and place in a deep bowl with a cover.
Pour Thousand Island dressing and lemon juice over meat and use enough to cover meat completely. Let stand for 3 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Place meat on skewers alternating it with vegetables.
Grill until meat is cooked over a low to medium flame.
Recipe given to me by Dr.
Aboosi.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well
mixed.
Freeze punch until slushy before serving.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Mix sauce and spices (to taste). Heat over medium to low heat until simmers.
In large bowl, mix noodles, sauce and cheese; mix well.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch or similar baking pan.
Cover and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread, etc.

title: forty-niners
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven and cool thoroughly before cutting into squares or bars.
Dust with powdered sugar, if desired.
(Chewy if eaten while warm.)

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook in double boiler.
Stir constantly until thick.
Spread on cake layers.

title: bacon and tomato potato skins
directions: Scrub and bake potatoes until tender; cool.
Halve each potato lengthwise; scoop out inside leaving 1/4-inch thick shell. Combine oil, chili powder and hot pepper sauce with a pastry brush.
Brush the insides of potatoes with oil mixture.
Cut the potato halves in half lengthwise.
Return to baking sheet. Sprinkle potato quarters with bacon, tomato and green onion.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and cut potatoes; boil in water with 1/4 teaspoon salt until tender. Drain potatoes and beat or mash until smooth. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until crust is brown and pie is set.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix together sausage, sage, egg and stuffing mix.
Form balls and brown in skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Put meatballs in crock-pot and pour mixture over them.
Turn on low heat and let cook until hot or ready to use.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil for 1 1/2 minutes, then add the following:

title: apricot cake (bundt)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cake mix and brown sugar in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a buttered and floured Bundt pan. Butter well or it will stick.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not overbake.
Turn out of pan immediately.
Cover loosely after cake has cooled.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or drizzle on favorite frosting.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend ingredients together in separate bowl.
Mix with first mixture.
Grease and flour 5 (1-pound) coffee cans.
Fill each 1/2 full of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: fricassee potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes into bite-size pieces.
Place in pot and cover with water.
Add diced onion, margarine and diced celery leaves. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Boil on low for about 20 minutes.
Tastes even better reheated.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and 1/2 cup crushed berries until thick and clear.
Add oleo and food coloring (enough for a bright red glaze).
Fill baked pie shell with remaining whole berries.
Pour sauce over berries.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, top with whipped cream.

title: corn custard casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and salt in the butter. Combine both cans of corn, eggs, muffin mix, milk and 1 cup of cheese. Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dijon sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Serve cold.
No fat, 11 calories and no cholesterol.

title: easy karo pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie shell. Bake in 350° oven 55 minutes. Chocolate Pecan Pie: Follow recipe for Pecan Pie. Melt 4 squares semi-sweet chocolate with margarine.

title: fast and easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain.
Combine with all but crackers.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle on top.
Put 2 tablespoons melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: vodka slush
directions: Combine water and sugar, bring to a boil.
Cool and add other ingredients to the sugar water.
Freeze in a large container.
The mixtures will never quite freeze, but remain mushy.
Serve in punch bowl.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Boil first four ingredients in water until tender, about 30 minutes.
Drain.
Add soup, milk, parsley, salt, pepper and cheese.
This is great on a cold, wintery day.
It can be easily doubled or tripled.
Better make lots of it because everyone loves it.

title: tortellini spinach soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine onion, carrots and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add tortellini, reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes. Meanwhile, clean, trim and coarsely chop spinach.
Add spinach and simmer 4 to 5 minutes longer until carrots are tender-crisp.
Add pepper to taste.

title: lemon yum yum
directions: Mix melted oleo to flour; add pecans and spread into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool. Mix 1/2 the Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Spread half on top of crust. Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut and 1/4 cup pecans over mixture. Mix pudding with milk and stir until thick. Spread over coconut and nuts. Top with remaining Cool Whip, coconut and nuts. Chill before serving.

title: chile cheese corn bread
directions: Thaw the corn.
Heat oven to 375° and butter a 9-inch cast-iron skillet or cake pan.
Cut cheese into slices about 1/4-inch thick.
Slice the peppers.
Combine corn meal, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the thawed corn.

title: macaroni salad with basil dressing
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine the basil, garlic, pepper and salt.
Process until finely chopped.
Add oil and vinegar.
Process until well blended.
Set aside.
In a 4-quart salad bowl, combine tomatoes, zucchini, macaroni and cheese.
Toss lightly.
Pour dressing over all and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: mud cake
directions: Melt butter with cocoa and add other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with miniature marshmallows and put in oven until melted.
Cool and ice.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Arrange strips of chicken in the bottom of a casserole dish. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Stir together soup and water in a sauce pan over medium heat to remove all lumps.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Stir in cheese and half of poppy seeds. Pour over chicken strips.
Mix together remaining poppy seeds, melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over chicken and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
(So good and fairly easy.)

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Arrange corned beef on 4 slices of bread.
Top each with a quarter of the sauerkraut, 2 Tbsp. of dressing and a slice of cheese.
Top with remaining bread.
In a skillet over medium heat, melt 2 to 3 Tbsp. butter.
Toast sandwiches until bread is lightly browned on one side.
Turn sandwiches and brown other side, adding more butter if necessary.
Cook until cheese is melted and meat is heated through.
Yield: 4 sandwiches.
Delicious!

title: beth's special chicken
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Dip chicken in this mixture and then roll in stuffing mix.
Place in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Pour 3 or 4 tablespoons melted butter over chicken and bake at 350° until chicken is done, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix these ingredients with the creamed sugar and shortening. Grease tube pan and flour.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes of 350°.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions and let cool. Meanwhile, prepare chocolate mousse according to package directions.
Break candy bars in small pieces in food processor. Break up brownies into small pieces.
Place in a large glass bowl or truffle dish.
Cover with half mousse, then half candy, then half whipped topping.
Repeat layers with the remaining ingredients.
Feeds up to 24 or 1 serious chocoholic!!!

title: potato and cheese soup
directions: Add water, pepper and beef flavor to stockpot.
Bring to boil. Turn heat down to low.
Stir in potato buds.
Cover and let stand 1 minute.
Add Beau Monde, cumin and butter.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in Cheddar cheese soup.
Cover and allow to return to simmer.
Dissolve arrowroot in 1 cup of warm light cream.
Stir into soup.
Gradually add remainder of light cream and sour cream. Cover and heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Makes about 10 quarts.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crumble cookies (save a little for top).
Mix with melted butter and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix well cream cheese and sugar.
Add 1/2 Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Spread on top of cookie mixture.
Prepare pudding as directed for pie.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with cookie crumbs.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add milk, then egg.
Stir real good.
Add 1/3 cup oil to an 8 or 9-inch frying pan.
Then pour about 1/2 of oil in mixture and stir real good.
Pour batter into pan.
Take spoon and pull oil up over batter.
Bake in 450° oven until golden brown.
Be sure middle is set.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown crumbs in skillet with butter.
Place half of bread crumbs in bottom of baking dish.
Place zucchini over bread crumbs then add peppers, onion, tomatoes and cheese in layers.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and top with bread crumbs.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Combine and bake at 325°
for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and melt.
Pour over Corn Chex or Crispix.
Mix in large bowl and put in a large bag.
Add 2 cups powdered sugar.
Shake well and add 2 more cups of powdered sugar. Shake well.
Pour out of bag into large bowl.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well while cooking until thick.
Put in pie shell and refrigerate.

title: stuffed peppers with hamburger
directions: Mix all ingredients in a frypan and cook hamburger until brown.
Set aside and cool.
Wash peppers, dry and cut out stems and seeds.
Stuff with hamburger mixture.
Place olive oil in frypan.
Very slowly fry peppers, turning often. Cook for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Put all ingredients in oven or microwave safe dish.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to recipe on box (or use your favorite yellow scratch cake recipe).
Put in 2 cake pans and bake according to directions.
Slice each layer with thread.
Mix 1 package coconut, sour cream, Cool Whip and sugar.
Put between layers, on sides and on top.
Sprinkle with 1 package coconut.

title: rolled shrimp sandwich
directions: Mix ingredients, using enough mayonnaise to give a good spreading consistency.
Cut crusts from thin sandwich bread. Spread with shrimp mixture.
Roll tightly, jelly roll fashion, in Saran freezer film or a slightly dampened paper towel.
Chill or freeze.
Slice thinly, about 1/2-inch.
Makes about 1 cup spread. Cutting 5 pinwheels per slice of bread,
makes about 50 sandwiches.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add baking powder, salt, vanilla and baking soda.
Alternate milk and flour.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fourth of july flag brownies
directions: Prepare and bake brownie mix as directed on package, using 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Mix sour cream and sugar until well blended.
Spread over baked brownies.
Decorate with strawberries and blueberries to create flag design.
Store frosted brownies in refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: never-fail frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla.
Bring to full rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Beat hard until smooth and shiny.
Pour and spread over cake.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops on both sides in skillet.
Remove chops and set aside.
Add water to make pan gravy from drippings.
Use this gravy alone or add cream soup (celery or mushroom) and onion.

title: broiled icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
If too runny, add more brown sugar.
Spread over cake.
Broil until bubbly.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in pan.
Take the batter which has been set aside and pour or spoon over peach mixture. Bake until golden brown approximately 40 minutes until top is brown and liquid is bubbling.
Test with a toothpick to see that cake portion is not gummy.

title: crabmeat stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and bake in a 450° oven until done.
Cut potatoes lengthwise, scoop out the pulp and mash with butter, cream, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Add onions and crabmeat. Fill the reserved shells with the mixture, and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pie crust
directions: In a bowl, mix flour and lard.
Stir egg and vinegar in a cup with salt.
Add to flour mixture enough water to make dough to roll out good.
This will make 2 crusts.

title: amazing american chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef in a large pot; add onion as soon as beef begins to brown.
Chop tomatoes into large pieces and add, with salt and pepper, to beef.
Cook over low heat.
In another pan, cook macaroni as directed on package, but reduce cooking time to 5 minutes.
Drain macaroni and add to tomato mixture; stir.
Add V-8 juice until it just covers macaroni and tomatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until macaroni is fully cooked and sauce is reduced, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco. Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavorings and butter.
Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve by itself or with toppings.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in a bowl.
Stir in picante sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Blend well.
Serve with corn chips or potato chips.
Add more picante sauce for a hotter taste.

title: oatmeal-coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir all filling ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Pour into pie shell; bake for 50 to 60 minutes, until top and crust are golden and a pick inserted in center comes out clean, but oily.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: water chestnuts wrapped in bacon
directions: Wrap a slice of bacon around a water chestnut that has been cut in half.
Secure with a toothpick.
Broil until bacon is done. After removing from oven, drain the bacon on a paper towel to remove excess grease.
Do this for as many as you would like.
Mix the chile sauce, mayonnaise, brown sugar and dry mustard together. Pour over bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tortillas
directions: Mix all together.
Fill tortillas.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: corn pones(mary abigale - ethel, gean parker)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
You can mix corn and enough milk or water to make like pancake consistency.
Fry in hot grease until brown (like pancake size).

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: party or shower mints
directions: Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar until good consistency.
Add peppermint to taste.
Roll in balls, then roll in confectioners sugar and push into mold.
These can be made ahead and frozen.

title: marylou's big 3-oh! cake
directions: Bake cakes as directed using two 9 x 13-inch pans; prior to baking add 1/4 cup of chocolate chips to each pan.
Cool.
Frost top on one layer with pudding, sprinkle with nuts and place second layer on top.
Frost entire cake with can of frosting.
Serve with good coffee!
Large cake, serves a lot of people.

title: cranberry swirl coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well (real creamy). Add flavoring.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream. Mix well until real creamy.
Pour 1/2 batter in bottom of Bundt pan (greased and floured).
Spoon all around 1/2 cranberry sauce and sprinkle with 1/2 the nuts.
Add rest of batter and repeat with remaining cranberry sauce and nuts on top.
Bake for 30 plus minutes in 350° oven.
You may glaze, sprinkle with powdered sugar or serve plain.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Scoop out loaf of Italian bread.
Cut bread into chunks.
Spread mixture into scooped out bread right before serving.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, butter and vanilla in blender.
Cover blender and blend on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato-potato chip casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix together all ingredients.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: south arkansas pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients with spoon.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then for approximately 40 minutes at 350°.

title: golden salad
directions: Heat 2 cups apricot nectar to dissolve jello.
Add drained juice from fruits to rest of nectar to make 3 cups cold liquid; add to jello mixture and chill slightly.
Mix fruits in cooled jello and pour in 11 by 9 inch pan.

title: "eggnog"
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and fluffy.
Then add sugar.
(Add brandy, then rum, if desired.)
Add milk and 3/4 of a half gallon of vanilla ice cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add to mixture, mixing well.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Better to let stand overnight.

title: cheese dip
directions: Beat until smooth and fold in the green onions.
Optional: Cut out top of round rye bread and fill with cheese mixture.
Cut up extra rye for dipping.
Make the night before.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar and drain a small amount of pineapple juice.
Mix ingredients together and turn into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until rises to the top and turns golden brown.

title: orange carrot cake
directions: Beat margarine until softened.
Add sugar and beat until light.
Stir together dry ingredients and add alternately with eggs to margarine-sugar mixture.
Stir in orange peel, carrots and walnuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Heat and stir marmalade.
Spread between layers and on top of cooled cake.
Refrigerate before slicing.

title: quick and zesty vegetable-beef soup
directions: In a large pot, brown the meat with the onion.
Cook until the onion is tender.
Drain off the grease.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, or until the noodles are tender.

title: fruit of the palm tree
directions: Put the ice cream and milk in the blender. Push each button for 10 seconds. Pour out and there's a good milk shake ready to drink.

title: maple mashed sweet potatoes
directions: Mix orange peel with mashed potatoes and place in a greased baking pan.
Mix butter with syrup and pour over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender and drain water.
Add cheese (desired amount) while macaroni is still warm and then add milk to top of macaroni.
Turn heat to low or simmer, cover and stir occasionally while it thickens.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: barbecue chicken and spareribs
directions: Pour over chicken and bake in roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, boiling water, raspberries and applesauce.
Mix sour cream and marshmallows together and spread on Jell-O after it has congealed.
Return to the refrigerator.
(Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.)

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Pour over dough.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: butterfish oriental
directions: Cut butterfish in serving pieces.
Marinate
in
Mirin, sugar and
shoyu.
When ready to serve, dredge
in
flour
or cornstarch and fry in oil until browned and crisp.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt butter and let set to room temperature.
Beat eggs until foamy; add flour, sugars and butter and beat well.
Add chips and nuts.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for one hour at 325°. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: low-fat pasta with pesto sauce
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients until well blended. Pour over 12 ounces hot fettuccine.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour this mixture over melted margarine or oleo, but do not stir.
Put fruit on top; sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar on top of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Wonderful!!

title: peanut butter cups (squares)
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, confectioners sugar, peanut butter, 2 sticks melted butter and vanilla. Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sherry's cheese bread(serves 8)
directions: Combine mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread on top of bread.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned raisin bars
directions: Combine water
and
raisins.
Bring
to a boil.
Remove from fire and
cool
to lukewarm.
Stir in salad oil.
Stir in sugar and
egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat into egg and raisin
mixture.
Stir
in	nuts and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake	in a moderate 375° oven until light brown. Cut in bars.
Dust
with
confectioners sugar.
Makes 2 dozen brownie size cookies.

title: spicy salsa
directions: Mix well all ingredients and chill.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Cook until it forms soft ball.
Cool.
Beat until spreading consistency.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed, making 2 layers.
Cool. Prepare instant pudding as directed; refrigerate.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil 9 cups water with 4 tea bags.
Add 2 cups of sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool and add orange juice, lemonade and brandy. Freeze.
To serve, spoon slush in glasses and add 7-Up to taste.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Pour off grease; add can of tomato soup, and 1 can water.
Let simmer about 8 to 10 minutes. Cook macaroni according to package.
When tender, add to skillet. Stir together; add cheese, stir and serve.

title: lemonade ice tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags.
Steep 5 minutes.
Add 4 cups cold water to make two quarts.
Add one 12 ounce can lemonade concentrate for each 2 quarts of tea.
Can add sugar to taste if you like a sweeter drink.

title: annie whisler's chocolate and vanilla caramels
directions: Chocolate Caramels:
Melt chocolate; add syrup and 1/2 pint cream.
Cook 10 minutes and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until soft ball stage on candy thermometer (255°).

title: zesty carrots
directions: Peel
and
cut	carrots lengthwise.
Cook until tender. Reserve liquid.
Arrange
in
a
shallow baking dish.
Combine horseradish,
onion,
carrot
liquid,
salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Pour over carrots.
Combine crumbs, butter and paprika and sprinkle over
top.
Bake
to 20 minutes in 375° oven. (May be prepared ahead and refrigerated for later baking. Add extra time for cold dish.)

title: lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Brown ground meat and drain excess fat. Add spaghetti sauce to ground meat. Pour 1/3 meat mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan. Add 1 layer of uncooked noodles, 1 layer of cottage cheese, 1/3 meat mixture and 1/3 of the Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers of noodles, ground meat mixture and remaining Mozzarella cheese. Top with grated Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour. Remove and let stand 5 minutes.

title: broccoli noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twinkies
directions: Beat cake mix, oil, eggs, pudding and water.
Spread into greased and floured jellyroll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Cool completely.
Cut in half.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Drain corn and enough cream to make 1 cup.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add liquid gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in corn and eggs.
Pour into a greased 10 x 6-inch casserole dish. Mix melted butter into crushed corn flakes and sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: standard butter 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream well together.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with the milk to the first mixture.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: quick 'n' easy stroganoff
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Open can (use two for more sauce) of soup.
Do not dilute!
Heat.
Add to pasta.
Stir in sour cream or dip to taste, about 1/4 cup.
Stir slightly to combine.
Serve with warm bread and green salad.
Takes about 15 minutes.
Serves 2 or 3 people.

title: minestrone
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Add fresh water and cook over low heat until soft.
Drain.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into a round pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Should not be brown or crisp. Cool.
Whip 2 cup of Cool Whip with cream cheese.
Spread on crust.
Mix fruit with strawberry glaze and place on top of cream cheese.
Refrigerate; cover with plastic or foil.
Can be served like pizza topped with additional Cool Whip.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg and vanilla. Sift flour and salt and add gradually to creamed mixture; add coconut and nuts. Butter a 9-inch square pan well; pat 1/2 of mixture in pan and press down well. Cover with jam; sprinkle remaining mixture over jam. Spread and press down very carefully. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes, until lightly browned. Cool completely before attempting to cut into squares. If not COOLED COMPLETELY, they will fall apart.

title: nacho dip
directions: Put hamburger, beans and bottle of hot catsup (may add Tabasco to taste if you want it hotter) in a pan and mix well. Chop the onion and green pepper.

Sprinkle 1/2 jar of olives, onions and green pepper over the top of the hamburger mixture. Then sprinkle 8 to 16 ounces of cheese on top of the peppers, etc. Cover with tin foil and heat in 200° to 250° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.
Dip freezes well.

title: mountain cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 6-inch baking dish.
Mix other ingredients except filling and pour into the butter.
Stir with spoon.
Dump the pie filling in the center of the milk and flour mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple and beets. Stir salad a couple of times while it is setting.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over carrots.
Refrigerate; eat cold or hot the next day.

title: pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water; drain.
Combine veggies, nuts and bacon with sour cream.

title: party meat balls
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Mix with the meat, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Roll into bite size balls and place in casserole dish.
Mix jelly and chili sauce together.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 40 to 50 meat balls.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast and egg.
Gradually stir in flour to form soft dough.
Beat vigorously; cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk. Punch down.

title: herbed rice
directions: Cook mushrooms in a skillet coated with cooking spray over medium-high heat until tender. Set aside. Dissolve bouillon granules in water. Combine bouillon, mushrooms, long grain rice and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 12 servings.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Slice tomatoes in wedges.
In small bowl whisk vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper until well blended.
Whisk in oil and parsley.
Pour over tomatoes.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Boil sugar and water about 10 minutes.
Cool syrup.
Add remaining ingredients except ice.
Pour into punch bowl.
Float pieces of ice and lemon slices on top of bowl.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, salt and milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir a moderate amount into eggs.
Immediately return to heat and cook 2 minutes.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Peel and cube eggplant; drop into boiling water.
Cook about ten minutes.
Drain, mash and set aside in glass bowl.
Saute chopped onions, green pepper and celery in butter for about 15 minutes.
Mix all together, reserving some cheese and crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Pour into greased baking dish; top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rocky road crunchy bars
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the peanut butter, 1/3 cup corn syrup and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Cook over low heat until the peanut butter is melted, stirring constantly.
Stir in the 2 1/4 cups of cereal until well coated.
Spread the peanut butter-cereal mixture into a greased 9 x 6-inch pan, pressing evenly into the pan; set aside.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple and bring to boil.
Remove from stove and cool completely.
When cool, mix remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix salt, sour cream, soup, Cheez Whiz, onion and 1/2 stick of butter, melted. Add potatoes. Pour into greased 9 x 13 dish. Melt remaining butter; mix with crumbs. Layer over mixture. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: reese's cups
directions: Combine crumbs, oleo, peanut butter and sugar.
Work together until smooth.
Press this mixture into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan or larger.
Melt chocolate of choice. Spread over crumb mixture. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: creamy tomato basil soup
directions: In a large saucepan in hot Wesson oil, saute the onion and garlic until tender but not brown.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended. Simmer uncovered 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and then pour soup, one third at a time, into the blender or food processor.
Puree until smooth. Makes 6 cups.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel apples and cut into small pieces.
Pour on sugar.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add oil.
Beat and add eggs and mix.
Sift dry ingredients all together, including nuts.
Fold into apple mixture.
Cook in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange juice pie
directions: Bring to a boil the orange juice, sugar and cornstarch.
When slightly thickened, remove from heat.
Add egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Pour in a baked pie shell.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Wash chicken breasts.
Lay flat.
Cut cream cheese into 4 square pieces.
Place 1 piece in center of chicken.
Chop green onions and sprinkle over each of cream cheese.
Roll chicken around cream cheese; wrap each with 1 to 2 slices bacon.
Serve with toothpicks.
Place in a square baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: caramel walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and egg; cut in 1/2 cup butter until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts. Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remainder of mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels with condensed milk and 1/4 cup butter.
Pour over crust.
Top with reserved crumb mixture. Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: banana crunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
In saucepan, melt butter, stir in frosting mix in rolled oats.
Stir until crumbly.
Add 2 tablespoons flour; set aside.
In large bowl, blend sour cream, eggs and bananas until smooth.
Blend in cake mix, beat 2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 batter (2 cups) into Bundt pan. Sprinkle with 1/3 of crunch mixture.
Repeat twice, ending with crumb mixture.

title: banana pudding no cook
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Add condensed milk and Cool Whip; mix well.
Layer wafers and sliced bananas; pour pudding mixture over.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat egg, then add juice from fruit cocktail and vanilla.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt; add to juice mixture. Fold in fruit cocktail.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine brown sugar and nuts; sprinkle evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold, plain or with cream or ice cream.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender but not browned.
Blend in flour and seasonings.Add milk and chicken stock and continue cooking until thickened, stirring frequently.
Fold in crabmeat gently and continue to cook for a few minutes until crab is heated through.
Garnish bowls of soup with chopped parsley.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt, flour, soda and apples together well.
Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Pour batter into pans (batter will be stiff).
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Take out of pans.
Sprinkle tops with sugar and cinnamon and wrap in foil while still warm.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fruit dip or dressing
directions: Mix sour cream with frozen orange juice with electric mixer until blended.
Sprinkle pudding over top and mix thoroughly. Chill.

title: indiana heath brunch coffee cake
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar with a fork or pastry blender. Reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture. Add buttermilk, baking soda, egg and vanilla to the remaining mixture.
Blend well the mixture and pour into the greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Mix together the crushed Heath bars and nuts.
Add to the 1/2 cup of reserved mixture and sprinkle over the top of batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in fruit, then topping. Freeze in large aluminum pan.
Freeze and cut into squares to serve.

title: papa's hot tomatoes
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes.
Put in jars; mash down until juice is at top.
Put in 1 medium pepper (jalapeno or chili) and 1/2 teaspoon salt per pint.
Put lids on.
Bring hot water bath to boiling, up to the lids.
Boil 35 minutes per pint.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Separate crescent rolls into triangles and press into shallow baking pan which has been greased.
Spoon sausage on top; sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with sharp cheese.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and sour cream until smooth. Add in picante sauce. Mix until well blended. Pour into a 9 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish.

title: irish rag
directions: Mix flour and baking powder and set aside.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add yolks and beat until fluffy.
Mix flour with sugar mixture and milk alternately.
Add vanilla and fold in beaten egg whites. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: healthy granola mix
directions: Measure just enough water to dissolve sugar and to moisten mixture. Mix all ingredients in bowl. Make sure the mixture is well coated. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes on a greased pan until golden brown.

title: chicken and rice and chestnuts
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix cream and mayonnaise. Spread on top.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix
together
in order given:
broccoli, chicken, Cheez Whiz, Cheddar
cheese, mushrooms, cream of chicken or mushroom soup, cooked rice and milk; and bake in baking dish at 350° for 1/2 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: hot chicken salad #1
directions: Mix; put in casserole dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes or potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: dessert breads
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in lukewarm milk.
Add 1 1/2 cups of flour. Beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise in warm place, free from draft, until light, about 3/4 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls (will double in size).
Grease pans. Bake for 5 minutes at 450°.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen (small).

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: chocolate banana cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, eggs, water and bananas.
Add in nuts, cherries and chocolate chips.
Bake as directed on box and enjoy!

title: zucchini cupcakes
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Fill paper baking cups 1/2 to 2/3 full with batter.
Sprinkle top of batter with sugar and cinnamon.
Top each with 3 or 4 chocolate chips.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes. No need to frost.
These also freeze well.
Makes 36.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown meat; add carrots and green onions.
Cook until carrots are tender (if using fresh ones).
Add cooked rice (cook rice in water).
Mix well.
Add soy sauce to taste.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Place ingredients in order given in blender jar. Mix until smooth. Pour into pastry shell and bake for 30 minutes or until firm in the center.

title: passover chocolate chip nut cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in oil until well blended.
Stir in nuts, chocolate, orange rind and salt.
Stir in matzo meal.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Drop batter by teaspoon on oiled pan dusted with matzo meal.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes until pale golden.
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen.

title: layered macaroni shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
In a large bowl, layer greens, macaroni, 1 1/2 cups of cheese, tomatoes, cut in wedges, shrimp, peas and cabbage.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients until creamy.
Alternate flour and milk, starting with flour.
Roll to 1/4-inch to 1/3-inch and cut into desired shapes.
Cookies can be frosted, if desired.

title: hearty taco pie
directions: Brown meat.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Unroll dough.
Press onto bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: panic spinach
directions: Put packages of spinach in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass pan so that they lean on the edge of the pan.
As spinach cooks, liquid will drain out the bottom.
Microwave on High for 9 to 10 minutes; drain and discard liquid and box.
Place spinach in dish and add dry soup mixed with sour cream.
Level.
Sprinkle stuffing over top.
Dot with margarine and top with cheese.
Microwave at 70% for 8 minutes or until heated through.
Serves about 6.

title: tortilla roll-ups (1)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Optional:
black olives, tomatoes, onions.
Roll up in tortilla shells & cut into sections. Serve with salsa & sour cream.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs, 3 Tbls. sugar and melted butter in 9-inch spring form pan, bake 325° for 10 minutes. Mix cream cheese, 1 c. sugar, flour and vanilla with mixer. Add sour cream mixing well, add eggs one at a time. Pour over crust. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until center is almost set. Cool before removing from pan and refrigerate.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Spread popcorn in a large shallow roasting pan. In a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan, stir together sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Continue cooking without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour corn syrup mixture over popcorn.
Stir to coat well.
Bake in 250° oven uncovered 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Break apart when cooled and store in tightly covered container.
Makes 1 pound.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix margarine and crackers.
Blend.
Spoon half in bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken bits on top.
Combine sour cream, broth and soup.
Stir.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken. Put rest of cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet 'n sour kielbasa(party favorite)
directions: Boil kielbasa in large saucepan.
Drain and remove kielbasa from pan and slice into desired serving size.
In same pan, add preserves, vinegar, soy sauce and dry mustard.
Bring to a simmer; stir until preserves has melted.
Add kielbasa and toss until well blended and hot.
May transfer to crock-pot.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: In a pan or wok heat oil on medium heat.
Saut garlic and chicken till chicken is completely cooked.
(Watch heat so that the garlic doesn't burn.)
In a separate pan scramble eggs till completely cooked.
When chicken is cooked add soy sauce, then the cooked rice.
Mix well, then add eggs.
Mix thoroughly and season with salt and pepper, onion powder and red pepper flakes if desired.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: wild mustang green grape pie
directions: Line unbaked pie crust with one layer of processed grapes, packing them closely together.
Combine flour and sugar (amount of sugar used depends on tartness of grapes) and spread evenly over grapes.
Pour cream over ingredients.
(The 1/3 pint of remaining grapes may be stored in liquid in which processed in refrigerator for later use.)
Bake slowly at approximately 350° for about one hour or until golden brown and filling thickens.
If cream browns too fast, lower temperature to 325° or 300°.
Cream burns easily and some ovens require a shorter baking time.
This is an unusual but very tasty pie, combining the tartness of the grapes with the sweetness of the cream and sugar.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese get to room temperature.
Mix with wire whisk into yogurt.
Wonderful with grapes, cantaloupe, kiwi, any kind of fruits or citrus.

title: lentil patties
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oil, but do not brown.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together well.
Form into small round cakes.
Brush top lightly with oil.
Brown in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve plain or with gravy.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add gradually, 1 egg at a time. Mix buttermilk and soda together and add alternately with flour. Add jam. Mix spices with flour. Add vanilla. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, carrots and onion in small amount of water.
Mash well. Add salt, pepper, sour cream, soup and pimento.
Grease casserole dish with butter and line with stuffing mix.
Pour mixture in and put rest of stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: parmesan cheese crisps
directions: Cover nonstick baking sheet with Silpat liner or parchment paper rubbed with olive oil, then sprinkles with flour.
Put a tablespoon of shredded cheese on the liner and flatten it slightly.
Repeat with remaining cheese, arranging the tiny piles as if they were cookies on the sheet; allow 1/2-inch between piles.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven or until cheese is bubbling and slightly browned.
Cool for 5 minutes, then lift the crisps from the sheets with a spatula and serve at once.
Can be kept for several days in an airtight container.

title: fancy fast chicken
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over chicken.
Mix can of soup with wine and pour over chicken.
Spread stuffing mix over top, then drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over medium heat to soft ball stage (232°), stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well until blended.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and shape into a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Store in refrigerator until firm.

title: bucket cake
directions: Layer the ingredients in this order: cake, pudding, strawberries, pie filing, Cool Whip.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix soups and Ro-Tel in blender.
Saute bell pepper, celery, onion, seafood and rice.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, flour, corn flour, Angostura aromatic B2itters, baking powder, the grated rind of the lime and coconut.
Mix well.
Bake at a moderate oven temperature for approximately 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: wagon wheel cookies
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend one egg at a time until mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Chill for several hours or overnight.
Drop teaspoonful of mixture in confectioners sugar and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix well the margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients and use wire whip on bananas. Combine all mixtures.
Bake in 2 (9 x 9-inch) round greased pans for 20 to 25 minutes.
While warm, brush on margarine or cool and frost with desired frosting.

title: famous corn casserole
directions: Bake uncovered in greased 9 x 12 pan on 350° for 35 minutes. Do not overcook!
It should be firm, not cake like.

title: grannie's pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt and water overnight.
Pour water off and pack cucumbers in jars.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and pickling spice; cook 5 minutes in hot water bath.

title: taffy
directions: Combine all except gelatin.
Boil to a hard ball.
Soak gelatin in cold water and add.
Remove from heat and cool.
Then it's ready to pull and pull.
Wrap in Handi Wrap.

title: easy yeast bread
directions: Pour the warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Add yeast; let stand a few minutes.
Add about 1/2 of the flour, sugar, salt and shortening.
Set mixer on medium speed and beat for 2 minutes, or until smooth.
Add rest of flour mixture.
Stir in by hand.
Cover bowl; let rise in warm place for about 30 minutes, or until double in bulk.

title: quick 'n easy potato dumplings
directions: Mix
mashed
potatoes,	flour,	egg, salt and pepper to form a soft
dough.
Shape
into a rope and cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Drop
into boiling water and remove when pieces float to top.
Fry in butter with onions and serve.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Add the three ingredients together and stir.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper and let set.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Stir sugar and cornstarch together, then combine all ingredients in saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Unroll crescent rolls, do not separate, press perforated seams together.
Spread sausage on top of dough and roll up.
Chill rolls until firm and slice.
Place on slotted broiler pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: applesauce-oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients; combine applesauce, eggs and butter. Stir dry ingredients into applesauce mixture alternately, blending well until moistened.
Stir in raisins and oats.* Spoon batter into greased muffin pans and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pans. Makes 2 pans or 1 1/2 dozen depending on size desired.

title: nut icebox cookies
directions: Mix together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs and vanilla, mixing in well. Stir in the flour mixture and the pecans.
Chill the dough until it is cool enough to handle (30 minutes to an hour).

title: c.h.s. home ec department's easy funnel cakes
directions: These two fruits combine beautifully to make a homey, warm-from-the-oven dessert.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach out and drain.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Mix all ingredients; refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours to let seasoning mix thoroughly.
Serve in a hollowed out loaf of sourdough bread with cut raw vegetables, crackers, etc.

title: oatmeal cookies(stay soft)
directions: Mix everything but oatmeal, flour, milk and raisins.
Blend well.
Stir in oatmeal and flour.
Last, stir in milk and raisins. Bake at 325° until done.
Do not brown.
Let cool slightly before taking off baking sheets.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients together.
Melt cooking wax with chocolate chips.
Shape first peanut butter mixture into balls. Dip into chocolate with a spoon and make sure it all coats.
Place on cookie sheet to dry.
Will look glossy when dry.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Add jello mix to hot sauce.
Let cool.
Fold sauce over strawberries and bananas.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Cut sauerkraut into short pieces with scissors.
Add sugar and let stand 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover bowl tightly and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
This salad will keep in the refrigerator for a week.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Steep tea bags in 1 cup boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Stir in sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Freeze firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Spoon into glasses; garnish with lemon wedges or lime, if desired.
Keep unused portion in freezer.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: tahiti salad
directions: Put together and mix.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: mexi-corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter, in a large cooking dish.
Add 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 cup instant rice. Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add corn and cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients and cover top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: marjorie's patties
directions: Make into patties and fry.

title: ruby alexander's fig cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs and add buttermilk and flour alternately.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans or 11 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: overnight salad
directions: Beat the egg until light and lemon colored.
Add lemon juice and sugar and cook in top of a double boiler over hot water until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat and cool.
Add fruit and marshmallows; fold in the cream.
Turn into individual molds, first rinsed with cold water.
Chill overnight. Unmold on lettuce.
Serve with a small amount of the whipped cream topped with a maraschino cherry.

title: dry cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large container such as a used ice cream bucket.
Store in a dry place.
For each cup of cocoa, use 1/4 cup dry mix to each cup of boiling water.
Serves roughly 32.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients well in large bowl.
Add the others one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir until smooth.
Put into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: candied potatoes
directions: Place sliced sweet potatoes and pineapple chunks alternately in baking dish.
Mix juice from pineapple with the pudding.
Mix and add the brown sugar.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook chicken until tender.
Remove broth.
Take chicken from bones and cut into small pieces.
Put 2 cups chicken broth and cream of chicken soup in a saucepan and bring to a boil.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sauce for vegetables
directions: Cream butter, cheese and salt.
Blend in sour cream, chives and cucumber.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
To serve, pour sauce over cooked vegetables while still hot.

title: meat balls, tarpon springs(keftedes)
directions: In a deep bowl, combine all ingredients, adding water if needed for a very soft mixture.
Knead to blend.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Shape lightly into 2 inch balls.
Roll in flour and brown in hot oil.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Start with a layer of chopped lettuce.
Add a layer of each of the following:

title: pineapple dish
directions: Mix.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve as a side dish with ham or pork.

title: pepper relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan. Bring to boil. Cook uncovered for 2 minutes. Pour into jars. Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a large casserole dish with Doritos.
Layer 1 cup Cheddar cheese on top of chips.
Brown ground beef, adding chili powder, pepper and garlic.
Drain beef. Drain beans and add to beef.
Add 1/2 jar salsa and 3/4 jar smooth taco sauce.
Add chilies.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour beef mixture into casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Add Doritos in crown-like fashion around side of dish.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Then add milk, egg and onion.
Beat until smooth.
Using a teaspoon, drop batter into 1/8-inch hot oil in frying pan.
Cook until golden brown and turn.
Cook again until other side is golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down slightly with fork tongs. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.
While still warm, lift onto rack to cool.
Makes 30 to 35 cookies.

title: frosty cappuccino cooler
directions: Blend condensed milk, Espresso powder, milk, nutmeg and ice cubes until smooth and frothy.
Pour into Irish coffee mugs or footed glasses or goblets.
Stir 1 ounce Irish cream liqueur into each serving, if desired.
Dust the top with a sprinkling of nutmeg.
Makes 3 cups, 2 servings.

title: open-face crab sandwiches
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Combine crabmeat and green onion in a medium bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and turn back one corner to vent.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Place muffin halves in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish.
Place lettuce and 1/4 cup crabmeat mixture on each muffin. Top with mayonnaise mixture, then slice of tomato.
Sprinkle with cheese and pepper.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 3 1/2 to 4 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: braciole
directions: Place the meat on the counter and pound it out a bit to tenderize and flatten.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

Place the pine nuts in a small frying pan and toast them over low heat until golden brown. Allow to cool and place in a small bowl with the mint, parsley, garlic, cheese, lemon juice and 1 tablespoon of the oil. Stir together and rub on the meat.
Roll the steak up tightly across the grain of the meat like a jelly roll. Tie the roll together with string to secure.
Season the outside with salt and pepper to taste.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in skillet.
Drain and add cubed Velveeta, Worcestershire sauce, oregano and garlic powder.
Stir until Velveeta is melted.
Drop by spoonfuls onto the party rye bread and top each with a slice of pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Can be put into plastic bags and stored in the freezer.

title: kathy's pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in bowl.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl.
Blend together.
Grease muffin tins or use baking cups.
Bake at 425° for 17 minutes; do not overbake.

title: pork chops
directions: Put sliced potatoes and onions in bottom of greased baking dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over potatoes. Top with grated cheese.
Lay pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave au gratin green beans
directions: Microwave butter and onion in a 2-quart casserole for 1 to 2 minutes until onion is tender.
Add flour, cheese and milk.
Stir well and microwave 4 minutes or until mixture is thickened.
Stir once each minute while cooking.
Fold in green beans and bacon. Top with cracker crumbs and microwave another 5 to 7 minutes, turning once while cooking.
Allow to stand 3 to 5 minutes before serving.

title: german potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
After cooked, peel and cut up. Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix pudding with 1 cup juice.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and pineapple.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Refrigerate at least overnight (or several hours).

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: In a skillet, combine the first 6 ingredients. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat for 10 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally. Brush one side of tortillas with butter. Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture over half of unbuttered side of each tortilla. Sprinkle with 1/3 cup cheese; fold plain side of tortilla over cheese. Place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 475° for 10 minutes or until crisp and golden brown. Cut into wedges; serve with sour cream and guacamole. Yield: 6 servings.

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Put in heavy pan (I use iron skillet) over low heat until margarine and sugar are melted. Turn up heat to medium and cook to soft ball stage when dropped in cold water, stirring to prevent sticking.
Cool 10 to
15 minutes.
Add vanilla. Beat until candy is no longer glossy. Add nuts and pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Cut bacon in pieces.
Brown bacon and chopped onion lightly. Add liquid drained from beans, and boil down to about 1/2 cup.
Add beans, sugar and vinegar; season to taste.
Heat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sarah's peanut butter pie
directions: Place powdered sugar in bowl.
Cut peanut butter in with pastry blender until crumbly.
Set aside 2 tablespoons for garnish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs into pie shell.
In a saucepan, combine 2/3 cup sugar,
1/3 cup cornstarch, egg yolks and milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter melts. Pour into pie shell.
In small saucepan, combine remaining sugar and cornstarch with water.
Cook over low heat until thickened. Cool slightly.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Note:
All ingredients are approximate, except yeast and salt and about a 3:1 ratio of flour to juice.

title: broiled fillet with garlic sauce
directions: Sauce: Mix
garlic in small dish with olive oil and let stand. Place
bouillon
in
uncovered
saucepan and cook over medium-high heat
until mixture is reduced to 1/2 the original amount.
Add
garlic mixture and sherry or cognac and continue to cook
for
10 minutes.
Serve over steak (also very good on baked potatoes instead of butter).

title: raw zucchini salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set for one day before serving.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Blend all together in pan, stir until boiling, then boil 3 minutes without stirring.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken, saving broth; debone and shred into bite size chunks.
Cook rice according to directions on box using 1 1/2 cups water and 1 1/2 cups broth.
After rice has set, add spices, tomato sauce, chili peppers and chicken.
Mix well.
Pour into a serving dish.

title: liverwurst ball
directions: Cream liverwurst and cream cheese.
Add next 4 ingredients and blend well.
Stir in beer gradually and beat until smooth. Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 3 cups.

title: antipasto
directions: Drain water from mushrooms, pimentos and olives.
Do not drain the artichokes; the oil is to be used to mix all the ingredients. Cut the salami, pepperoni and Provolone into 1/4-inch slices. Then dice into bite size pieces and mix together.
Cut the remaining ingredients into bite size pieces and add.
Mix well before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Work all ingredients together with hands.
Roll into 2-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: *chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and fold in Cool Whip.
Place layer of graham crackers, then layer of pudding mix.
Repeat, ending with graham crackers on top.
Frost the top with chocolate icing.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: 3 month pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and fill a gallon jar.
Add alum, salt, spice and enough vinegar to cover the cucumbers.
Set aside for 3 months. Then pour off vinegar and slice about 1/4- inch thick; layer slices back in the jar.
Add sugar; turn jar back and forth or shake until sugar is dissolved.
They are ready to eat.

title: hamburger monterey
directions: Dice bacon and fry until crisp; reserve.
Shape beef into tiny balls.
Cook in bacon fat until brown; remove.
Slice onion and dice pepper; cook until lightly browned.
Add beans, tomato soup, chili powder, macaroni and salt; simmer 10 minutes.
Grate cheese. Add.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add bacon and meat balls; simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 2 prepared pie shells.
Bake at 500° for 8 minutes, then lower temperature to 325° and bake until firm.

title: butter mints
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in sugar and shape or flatten.
If creamier mints are desired, substitute canned milk (condensed) instead of water.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cook corn according to directions and drain well.
Add margarine, cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Bring to boil to melt cheese and thicken sauce.

title: chilled fruit pie
directions: Cook until thick sugar, flour, juice from can of cherries and pineapple.
When mixture is thick, add cherries and pineapple, cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, add jello (dry), food coloring, bananas and nuts.
Mix and pour into baked pie shells or graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, cook sugar and corn syrup on High 4 minutes.
Stir in roasted salted peanuts.
Cook on High 3 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook on High 1 minute and 20 seconds.
Add baking soda.
Stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture on greased cookie sheet.
Let stand 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes 1 pound of brittle.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix crab meat, onion, celery and pickle together.
Mix well and add to crab mixture the mayonnaise or salad dressing (start with 1/2 cup and add to your liking), mustard, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and salt.
Chill thoroughly.

title: baked stew
