directions: Combine in large kettle (do not brown meat as usual in stews). Bake in oven 5 hours at 250°, 7 hours is better (but at least until done).
Stir occasionally.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake in a greased casserole dish for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple in pan and spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread evenly.
Dump dry cake mix on cherry layer.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Put butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Add flour to shortening in preheated deep skillet or 5-quart Dutch oven and cook on medium heat until a rich, dark brown, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp, seasoning to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: nutty peach squares
directions: In a large bowl, beat margarine and sugar at medium speed until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; stir in vanilla wafer crumbs.
Stir crumb mixture with milk into margarine mixture until well blended.
Stir in peaches and walnuts.
Spread into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Top squares with peach slices and a dollop of whipped topping.

title: country casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Combine noodles, chicken soup, peas and carrots, celery, onions (after topping; reserve 1/2 can for topping), cheese, milk and seasoning.
Pour in casserole.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: cinnamon sweet rolls
directions: Scald milk, sugar, salt and oleo.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure water in large bowl.
Dissolve yeast; add milk mixture, eggs and 1/2 of flour.
Beat until smooth; add rest of flour to make slightly stiff dough.
Knead on floured board about 8 minutes. Place in greased bowl; let rise 1 hour.
Punch down.
Roll out in rectangle.
Spread with 1/4 oleo; sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 to 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll up like jelly roll, then cut into 1-inch slices.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Frost with 10x sugar and milk.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage fine.
Add salt, pepper and sliced apples.
Heat fat in heavy skillet and add cabbage and apples.
Pour boiling water over to cover and cook until tender.
Sprinkle flour over cabbage and add sugar and vinegar.
Let simmer a little longer.

title: bea's party punch
directions: Pour pineapple juice into punch bowl; add the ice cream and sherbet by small amounts at a time.
Add ginger ale and stir slightly.
Serve punch immediately.
Yields about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: quail or dove in mushroom sauce
directions: Wash venison; remove all white skin possible.
Marinate tenderloin in Italian dressing for 8 to 12 hours, piercing meat with sauce and turning every hour or so.
Cook on low heat on grill, basting with mixture of 1 cup oil with 4 tablespoons lemon juice very 15 minutes.
Cook until tender or done as desired.

title: chili velvet rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
In buttered casserole layer rice, cheese, green chilies and sour cream.
Continue to layer ingredients; will make three layers.
Top with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple icing
directions: Let cook until thickens.
Cool and put on yellow cake.

title: cora's fudge cake
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix cocoa and flour.
Add buttermilk and flour mixtures alternately to creamed sugar and Crisco.
Grease and flour 3 round cake pans.
Pour in batter and bake in a 350° oven until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sweet bread
directions: Mix yeast and warm water in large bowl.
Beat eggs and sugar 3 minutes.
Heat milk until lukewarm, add butter and salt.
Add to eggs and sugar, mix together.
Then add to yeast mixture, start adding flour.
Cover, let rise in warm spot for 4 to 6 hours. Punch down, put in greased and floured pans.
Cover and rise again 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: phluffy cake icing
directions: Slowly add instant pudding to milk, stirring continually. Quickly add Cool Whip before pudding thickens.
Mix until Cool Whip lumps are smoothed into pudding.
Spread onto a cooled cake and allow it to set in the refrigerator.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cocktail.
Cook 1 1/2 cups juice and 1 box noninstant vanilla pudding until thick.
Cool. Add fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Drain cherries and oranges before adding.
Keeps well overnight.
If desired, add bananas, cut up, before serving.

title: rum raspberry mousse
directions: Sprinkle 2 teaspoons raspberry gelatin powder over 1 tablespoon cold water in a cup.
Stir and let stand one minute to soften.
Add 2 tablespoons boiling water and the rum extract.
Stir until dissolved.
Beat the sugar, heavy cream (very cold) and 2 teaspoons vanilla extract in refrigerated mixing bowl.
Mix at medium speed until stiff peaks form.
Add gelatin mixture and beat until blended.
Mold, chill, garnish, serve and eat.
Enjoy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat & stir until heated through. Stir in rice & broccoli.
Pour into buttered casserole & bake.
I sometimes sprinkle Italian bread crumbs over top before baking.

title: pineapple oatmeal bread
directions: Grease bottom only of loaf pan.
Mix sugar, oleo, eggs and pineapple in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients except oats and nuts.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan; remove and cool completely before slicing.
Store tightly wrapped in fridge.

title: first grade pie
directions: Break apart chocolate bar and melt.
Stir in coconut, oleo and water.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into a baked pie crust.
Chill in freezer several hours or overnight.
Additional Cool Whip may be placed on top when serving.

title: elegant green beans
directions: Combine soup, onion, oregano and sour cream.
Mix with green beans.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: alabama sirloin strips
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, except steak.
Mix well.

title: filled cookies
directions: Soak all ingredients awhile with pinch of salt.
Let come to a boil and cool.
Roll dough about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut cookies. Put teaspoon of filling on one cookie, put another cookie on top pressing edges well.
Cut a little hole in top to allow steam to escape.
Bake in 350° oven until a nice brown.
Do not overbake.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in oblong cake pan at 350° until done.

title: stir-n-drop sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs with fork until well blended. Stir in oil, vanilla and lemon flavor; blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and stir into oil mixture.
Drop with teaspoons 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with greased glass bottom dipped in sugar. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or just until a delicate brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: *Made with 1 cup 1% low-fat cottage cheese, blended with 2 tablespoons of plain nonfat yogurt and 2 tablespoons of lemon juice in a blender.

title: coconut icing
directions: Mix together and spread on cooled cake layers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dutch crumb cake
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift with salt and spices. Combine with sugar and shortening. Mix to a crummy consistency. Combine water, molasses and baking soda. Add crumbs, saving 1/2 cup for top of cake. Beat until smooth. Pour into well oiled pan. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Bake in a moderate oven at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix undiluted soups together.
Add white wine and thoroughly mix.
Add long grain rice packet and seasonings.
Mix well. Allow to set 2 hours in the bowl.
Grease roasting pan which should be 2 inches high.
Spread rice mixture over the bottom. Place chicken pieces, from which you remove the skin, down on top of the rice.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for one hour.
Remove foil.
Turn chicken and bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour more.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes; be sure to do this.
Mix the next 3 ingredients and combine with the beaten eggs.
Sift together remaining ingredients and fold into egg and pumpkin mixture.
Line 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet with waxed paper. Pour mixture on the waxed paper.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Dump out on 2 paper towels sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Peel off waxed paper and roll up about 3 rounds.
Let cool 20 to 30 minutes.
Unroll very carefully and spread with the filling mixture.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, together until well blended.
Fold in egg whites and fill unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 25 minutes.
This is like a cheese cake.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add egg yolks, add milk alternatly with flour, salt, baking powder (sifted together).
Melt chocolate in double boiler, add baking soda, boiling water (mixture will fizzle up).
Let settle and cool slightly.
Mix with cake batter. In small bowl beat the egg white until stiff.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour cake into 9-inch cake pans or 13 x 9-inch loaf pan. greased and floured pan).
Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes.

title: green jello salad
directions: Dissolve and stir well the 2 cups of jello in boiling water. When dissolved well and the mix has cooled, stir in mayonnaise and add other ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: lasagna
directions: In medium bowl, combine sauce and ground meat.
In a separate medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Pour 3/4 cup sauce mixture in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer one-third of the noodles, half of the Ricotta mixture, 1/3 of the remaining sauce and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese in pan. Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles, sauce, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruited rice pudding
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
In saucepan combine rice, water, syrup and salt.
Mix just to moisten rice.
Bring quickly to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add marshmallows, pineapple, banana and lemon juice.
Cool thoroughly. Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter chocolate squares
directions: Melt 2 sticks butter.
Add confectioners sugar, graham cracker crumbs and jar of Jif to melted butter.
Mix until pasty.
In glass or aluminum baking casserole, grease bottom with spray or margarine.
Form peanut butter mixture in pan and even out.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over top of mixture.
Refrigerate for approximately 30 minutes, then cut into squares.
Arrange and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: broiled crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix well and spread on small (2 x 2-inch) party rye bread. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 15 minutes until brown.
Makes approximately 30 slices.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Mix together, pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pinball wizard(carmine-pink thick buttermilk refresher)
directions: Whiz yogurt, juice and sweetener in a blender.
Pour into a glass and sprinkle ground cloves on the top.

title: crispy chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine cereal, flour and seasonings. Place butter in another bowl. Dip chicken in butter, then into cereal mixture. Place in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan. Drizzle with remaining butter. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: watergate cake
directions: Blend all in large bowl; mix 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Split into 3 pieces.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole with tight fitting lid.
Cover first with foil, then lid.
Cook at 300° for 3 hours. Serve over buttered noodles or rice.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients, then nuts and pineapple.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Divide in 2 well-greased loaf pans (grease and spray, sticks easily).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Mix as named and add pepper last.
May not need that much pepper, depends on taste.

title: good luck beans
directions: Mix 1 pound of each type of bean.
Rinse 1 1/2 cups of mixed beans.
Soak overnight in water.
Drain and add 2 quarts of water and at least 1 teaspoon salt.
Add ham.
Cook slowly for 3 hours. Add onion, garlic, Ro-Tel tomatoes and lemon juice.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Serve with hot cornbread.

title: corn meal poultice(home remedy for man or beast)
directions: Open the boil with a sterilized needle.
Use a flame to sterilize the needle.
Take a thin slice of raw onion and put on boil.
Use a white cloth; wrap up the place.
Change every few hours.
Keep the boil open and draining.
Keep it clean all around it.
Take showers instead of baths to reduce the chance of spreading the infection.

title: jiffy chicken or turkey pie
directions: Prepare chicken or turkey.
Mix broth, chicken soup and margarine. Set aside.

title: scalloped lobster
directions: In large bowl, mix preceeding ingredients in order given.
Put in a greased baking dish and cover with crumbs.
I use Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until hot.
It's delicious.

title: marbled andes brownies
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Prepare brownies mix as directed.
Spread into pan.
Bake as directed.
Immediately place unwrapped candies on surface of hot brownies.
Allow to stand 3 to 4 minutes or until candies are melted.
Using knife or metal spatula, gently swirl melted candies to cover entire surface of brownies.
Cool 2 hours or until just set.
Cut into bars. Makes 2 dozen.

title: dump cake
directions: Into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, dump pineapple.
On top of pineapple, dump cherry pie filling.
On top of pie filling, dump dry cake mix.
On top of cake mix, dump pecans.
Over the whole thing pour melted butter.
Do not stir.
Spread each layer evenly in pan as you add ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve from pan the cake is baked in.

title: hot fudge
directions: In a sauce pan over low heat, melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth.

title: crescent caramel rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat bottom and sides of large Bundt pan with butter; sprinkle pan with 3 tablespoons nuts.
Melt margarine in small saucepan; add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove crescents from can in rolled sections; do not unroll.
Cut each section into 4 slices.
Arrange 8 slices in prepared pan, separating each pinwheel slightly to allow sauce to penetrate.
Spoon half the caramel sauce over dough.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Pour remaining caramel sauce over dough; bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 3 minutes.
Turn into serving platter or waxed paper.

title: red cabbage
directions: Over medium heat in heavy saucepan, saute onion in bacon drippings until clear.
Add wine, sugar, vinegar and garlic. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cabbage; cover and simmer another 20 minutes.
Add apples and simmer, stirring often, until cabbage and apples are tender.
Season with salt and hot sauce.

title: chex and chocolate party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix dry ingredients in a roasting pan. In saucepan, heat sugar, butter and corn syrup to boiling.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Bake one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool, then add chocolate bits and raisins.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn.
Set aside, but keep warm.
Butter the bottom and sides of a medium-sized saucepan.
Mix the honey, white Karo syrup and sugar in the saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add the peanut butter and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Pour over popcorn and stir until all popcorn is covered.
Let cool for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: peppers popcorn balls
directions: In saucepan combine molasses, sugar and water. Cook to soft ball stage, stirring frequently. Pour over popcorn and mix. Cool slightly. Shape into balls with buttered hands.

title: polish wedding cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Chop or cut up apricots and place in saucepan with 1 cup of water.
Place over medium heat.
Bring to boil.
Cover and turn down to simmer for 30 to 45 minutes or until apricots are very soft.
Mash well and add 2 tablespoons sugar. Stir and set aside,

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Remove.
Add baking soda.
Stir quickly and pour onto buttered pan.
Spread evenly.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes approximately 1 pound.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Hull the strawberries; save half for bottom of pie shell. Mash other half, add sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well and cook until clear and thick, stirring constantly so mixture will not stick.
Cool strawberry mixture and baked pie shell.
Line cooled pie shell with uncooked berries, flat side down.
Pour cooled berries mixture over all.
Top with whipped cream.

title: crullers
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine, mixing until well blended. Add flour and salt; mix well.
Shape dough into ball; chill 1 hour.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix all together, then chill for 30 minutes. Roll on flour surface.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook carrots and celery in boiling water until tender.
Do not drain.
In skillet, cook onions and butter until tender.
Stir in flour, gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add broth, cheese, carrots and celery.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.

title: zucchini and tomato casserole
directions: Saut onion, zucchini, green peppers and all seasonings in 3 tablespoons butter.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Add tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese and bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: tomato soy
directions: Mix the tomatoes, onions and salt.
Let stand overnight.

title: pistachio chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Sprinkle chips and pecans over bottom of pan.
Mix cake ingredients except chocolate syrup and confectioners sugar in usual manner in order given.
Reserve 1 cup batter.
Pour remaining batter into pan.
Add chocolate syrup to reserved cup of batter and pour over top of white batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan 30 minutes.
Turn out and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: meaty cheese ball
directions: Season to taste with seasoned salt.

title: mustard wiener bits
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add wieners and simmer at least 1 hour before serving.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix onion and raw ground beef (salt and pepper to taste).
Press raw mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Cover with raw sliced potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Bake, uncovered, at 375 degrees for one hour.

title: white salad
directions: Heat marshmallow and milk at low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in cream cheese until melted, add cottage cheese and pineapple, fold in cherries and oranges.
Fold in cool whip.
Put in serving dish, cover well. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain grease off hamburger and add other ingredients.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked egg noodles or chow mein noodles.

title: california carrots
directions: Pare carrots. Cut diagonally in thin slices. Combine with raisins, water and salt in a medium-size heavy saucepan.
Cover.

title: deep dish chicago pizza
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, heat sausages and 1/4 cup water to boiling.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove cover and continue cooking 20 minutes.

title: anita harrison's favorite
directions: Call favorite restaurant for reservations!!!!

title: layered cream cheese and strawberries
directions: Combine crackers and butter; press into bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Chill.

title: hershey cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add chocolate syrup.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately to egg mixture with buttermilk. Add vanilla and melted Hershey bars.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
May be served with Cool Whip.

title: honey apple cake
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar, oil and honey.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to the honey mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Add vanilla, nuts and apples.
Mix gently and pour into large cake pan which has been greased and lightly floured.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian beef
directions: Place meat, seasonings, peppers and juice in crock-pot. Cover with water.
Cook for at least 4 hours before you shred meat into small pieces.
Cook for 2 more hours, until tender.
Serve shredded meat on buns with cheese on top.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a blender, crush cookies until fine; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, butter and sugar until smooth.
In another bowl, mix pudding and milk until well blended.
Fold into cream mixture.
Fold in whipped topping.
Alternate layers of cookie crumbs and pudding mixture, ending with crumbs.
Chill overnight. Can be put in a clean flowerpot and decorated with silk flowers and gummy worms.

title: broiled chicken parmesan
directions: Remove any skin and fat from chicken. Place chicken on broiler pan and sprinkle with lemon juice and cheese. Dust lightly with paprika. Broil 10 minutes or until just cooked through. Makes 4 servings.

title: slow cooker caramelized onions
directions: Cut onions in half; cut each half into 1/2-inch thick slices. Combine all ingredients in a 3 1/2-quart slow cooker.
Cook, covered, at HIGH 8 hours or until golden brown and very soft.

title: baked ham sandwiches
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with bread slices.
Melt butter; stir in poppy seed and mustard.
Spread 1/2 butter mixture over bread.
Cover with ham slices; top with bread slices.
Spread with remaining butter mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: second hand sweet pickles #2
directions: Drain pickles.
Add sugar and replace lid.
Set jar upside down in bowl.
Refrigerate or a few days, then turn right side up for about a week.

title: holiday wassail
directions: I use my 30 cup coffee maker, which is a percolator, to make the Wassail.
Put the apple cider in the bottom of the coffee pot. Add the rest of the ingredients into the basket at the top.
Plug in the coffee maker and allow it to perk.
When it stops, the Wassail is done, and it will stay hot during the time you need it. Serve in glass or china cups.
Brandy can be added at this time if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: robin's jewish penicillin(chicken barley soup)
directions: Simmer chicken, sliced carrots, chopped celery and chopped onion in large pot with salt and pepper.
As chicken is boiling, skim top with slotted spoon to remove unwanted fat.
After chicken has simmered for about 1 hour, drain liquid and save.
Allow chicken to cool and pull off bones.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
Stir fruits into jello liquid.
Pour half the jello mixture into an 8-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.
Keep remainder of jello mixture at room temperature.
Spread congealed mixture with 1 cup sour cream. Spoon remaining jello mixture (room temperature) over sour cream and refrigerate until firm.
Top with remaining sour cream, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: katie's 3 bean bake
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion; drain.
Fry bacon, drain, and chop in fine pieces.
Combine all ingredients and bake in a covered 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Mix sugar, salt and flour. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of this mixture over bottom of pastry. Arrange half the peaches in the pastry shell.
Sprinkle with half the remaining sugar-flour mixture.
Arrange remaining peaches, then sprinkle with rest of sugar mixture.
Combine melted margarine and lemon juice.
Drizzle evenly over peaches in shell. Cut remaining pastry in strips 1/2-inch wide and arrange crisscross on top of fruit.
Turn edges of pastry under and crimp or flute as desired.
Bake in moderately hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and continue baking 30 minutes.
The little trick of flavoring with lemon juice and margarine works well with other fruit and berry pies.

title: world's best layer salad
directions: Top generously with small dabs of mayo; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Repeat for desired amount.
Sprinkle crisp bacon on top layer.
Do not toss; serve layered.

title: smoked sausage and bean soup
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, cook the onion and garlic in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add the water, potatoes, sausage, beans and bouillon granules.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Add the cabbage, catsup and vinegar. Simmer, covered, 10 minutes or more.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and chill overnight. If desired, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss apples, celery and nuts with mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce.
Top each serving with a maraschino cherry.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese koogle
directions: Mix together all ingredients. You may wish to put cinnamon in mixture or sprinkle it on the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can be frozen when cooked.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine milk, 1/2 of margarine, sugar and salt in a saucepan. Heat until margarine is melted.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Stir in yeast until dissolved.
Place flour in a large bowl.
Make a well in the flour and pour in liquid mixture.
Stir until blended. Cover and let rise until double in bulk (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: carrot oatmeal muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add brown sugar, milk, egg and oleo.
Mix thoroughly.
Add the carrots and oats.
Mix well. Spoon the batter into greased muffin pan cups.
Fill them 2/3 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Stir soup until creamy.
Add milk, cheese and onion, then macaroni, beef and eggs.
Turn into a 1-quart baking dish. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Measure all ingredients in a large mixer bowl; beat on medium speed 1/2 minute, scraping side and bottom of bowl constantly.
Pour into pan or pans.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly on wire rack before slicing.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter; cover with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seafood sauce and pasta
directions: Prepare macaroni as label directs, but don't use salt in the water.
Meanwhile, cook ground beef until well browned.
Stir in taco seasoning mix and 1 cup water; heat to boiling, stirring until blended.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and crumble the sausage.
Use 13 x 19-inch baking dish. Make first layer crumbs, second layer sausage and third layer cheese.
Then alternate layers.
Beat eggs, salt, pepper and mustard and blend with milk.
Pour mixture over the layered casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Before serving, cut into squares.
Yields 12 servings.

title: potato risotto
directions: Melt butter in a 2 or 3-quart pan over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic and thyme.
Cook, stirring often, until onion is soft.
Add broth; bring to boil over high heat.
Then boil uncovered until mixture is reduced to 1 1/2 cups.
Add potatoes and cook over medium heat uncovered, stirring often, until potatoes are tender to bite, about 25 minutes.
Remove from heat and mix in cream and cheese.
Season to taste with salt.
Pour into 10-inch rimmed baking pan.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours until light golden.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: inexpensive cookies
directions: Mix well and roll into balls.
Bake on greased baking sheet in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet while still warm.

title: shrimp-rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, cheese and shrimp (reserve some cheese for top). Mix egg yolks and milk; combine with shrimp mixture.
Season with pepper, onion salt and dill weed.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle reserved cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Divide and place in 2 loaf pans.
Make trench in top of meat and pour approximately 2 tablespoons ketchup in trench.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
One-third of meat can be lean pork sausage.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well except chocolate and paraffin in large bowl.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip balls in melted chocolate and paraffin.
A wire spoon or slotted spoon works well.
Cool on wax paper.
Can be frozen.
Makes 120 to 150.

title: crab salad
directions: Boil pasta until done. Rinse with cold water; drain. Dice bell pepper, onion and eggs. Combine with pasta, crabmeat, tuna, mayonnaise and seasonings. Chill and serve.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Blend well.
Spray a baking pan with Pam.
Pour in mixture and add fruit to top.
Bake at 375° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: tuna mousse
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine the gelatin, lemon juice, onion and boiling water and blend thoroughly.
Add mayonnaise, tuna, paprika and dill - blend again.
Add sour cream and blend making sure the mixture is smooth and that the sour cream has all been incorporated.
Turn mixture into a lightly oiled 3 1/2 cup mold (I use a fish shaped mold).
Chill until firm, preferably overnight and unmold on a platter (it helps to loosen the edge with a small sharp knife).
Garnish with parsley, black olives, green olives, radishes and lemons (I use a small piece of a sliced green olive with pimento for fish's eye.)
Surround the bottom of the tray with party sized pumpernickel or rye bread slices or crackers.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix salad oil and sugar; add eggs.
Add all other ingredients as listed.
Bake in a large 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° or until done.
Make icing; pour over cake while hot.

title: rice
directions: Boil a piece of fresh ham or Boston butt in water.
When it is almost done, turn heat to low and let water cook out.
Let meat brown, turning often.
When meat is brown, pour a small amount of water over meat.
Use this liquid to cook rice.

title: baked salmon("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Put casserole in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Insert knife to test, until it comes out clean.

title: egg salad spread
directions: Place all ingredients except eggs into blender.
Quarter eggs and separate white from yolks.
Add yolks to blender.
Cover and blend on chop or low until ingredients are chopped.
Stop blender and push mixture toward blades with rubber spatula.

title: berry pudding
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.

title: lite peach cream pie(serves 8)
directions: Using blender or electric mixer, combine gelatin and boiling water.
Blend on low speed 1 minute; blend on high speed 1 minute. Add marshmallow, blending well.
Mix in yogurt.
Pour into medium bowl.
Refrigerate until almost set, 2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: carol's chili
directions: Brown bacon and sausage.
Set aside.
Brown beef and drain. Cook onion, pepper, garlic and jalapeno pepper over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in wine and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mash tomatoes.
Add tomatoes and juice and all meats to onion mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1/2 hour, covered.
Stir in all beans.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serves 15.

title: persimmon spoon pudding
directions: Mix beaten eggs with pulp. Add sugar. Sift flour, soda and salt. Add alternately to mixture with milk. Add 2 tablespoons melted butter. (The mix will be quite thin.) Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 350° oven in a large ovenproof bowl or casserole or until dark (like chocolate) and grainy, but not dry.
You must stir every 15 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Separate rolls and press them out into a glass pie pan. Thinly slice the zucchini and onion.
Saute zucchini and onion ringlets in butter until about half done.
Put half the veggies into the pie pan crust.
Add half of the cheese; repeat.
Bake according to roll recipe (400° for 12 to 15 minutes).

title: fruit and angel dessert
directions: Tear cake into bite size pieces.
You should have about 8 cups.
Arrange half of the cake pieces in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with half of the undrained pineapple and half of the cherries. Spread half of the whipped topping over all. Sprinkle half of the coconut on top. Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve chilled.
Serves 12.

title: deviled peanuts
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish combine peanuts, oil, chili powder, salt and red pepper.
Spread evenly in baking dish.
Cook peanut mixture at High for 15 minutes, until toasted, stirring 4 times.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: birds nest pie
directions: Put margarine in dish in oven at 425°.
Mix ingredients together and pour into dish.
Bake for about 5 minutes and add fruit.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in Bundt or angel food cake pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove cooled cake from pan.
Use a toothpick to punch holes in cake so it will absorb the sauce.

title: cheese soup
directions: Simmer vegetables for 15 minutes in broth until done.
Add milk and flour.
Add cheese last.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle onions over.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over hash browns.
Melt butter, pour on top. Add salt and pepper, grated cheese and sprinkle corn flakes on top. Bake at 350° 1 hour.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute, then remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 100.

title: sauteed vegetable medley
directions: In a large saucepan, in water to cover, bring potatoes to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes, until barely tender.
Drain and set aside.
In large skillet, heat oil and butter.
Add zucchini; cook, stirring 3 minutes until tender, with slotted spoon.
Remove to bowl and set aside.
Add potatoes to skillet; saute until lightly browned.
Return zucchini with remaining ingredients to skillet; heat through.
Serve hot.

title: cherry cream freeze
directions: Combine lemon juice and condensed milk.
Add cherries and pineapple.
Fold in the whipped cream or Cool Whip gently.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover with foil and freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form in a ball shape.

title: baby fozzie's dump cake
directions: Mix all with fork in pan until lumps are out.
Don't work out bubbles.
Bake 20 minutes in oven at 350° on oven rack in middle in 8-inch square pan.

title: cherry bomb
directions: Combine rum, lime soda, grenadine and lime juice. Mix well. Garnish with cherry and lime slice.

title: apple stack cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each egg addition.
Sift flour with soda, baking powder and salt; add to batter, starting with flour and alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Chill dough 4 to 5 hours.
Divide into 6 or 7 portions.
Roll out layers on floured board; bake on cookie sheet at 450° until light brown.
Spread each layer with dried apple filling.
Do not spread filling on top layer.
Let stand in a tight container for at least 12 hours before cutting.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Sift flour and salt together and fold into mixture.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
This may be baked in 2 loaf pans.
Serve plain or with ice cream, strawberries or peaches.
Slices may be spread with butter and toasted under broiler.

title: ragu meat loaf
directions: You will also need waxed paper.

title: quick grape jelly
directions: Cook grape juice to a rolling boil.
Pour over sugar and stir until dissolved.
Ready for sterilized jars.

title: christmas jello salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup hot water, then add 1 cup water and pineapple juice, combined.
Let set in a 9 x12-inch dish.
In double boiler, melt marshmallows and cream cheese.
Cool, then add the whipped cream and pineapple.
Pour over lime jello.
Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water. When it starts to thicken, pour over top of rest of salad.
Chill.

title: chili
directions: Simmer at least 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger, onion, garlic and salt together until brown. Cook lasagna noodles until tender.
Add Ragu and tomato sauce to hamburger mixture; simmer 10 minutes.
Cook butter, milk and flour together to make a white sauce.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan layer noodles, hamburger, white sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until melted together.
Add gelatin, stir until dissolved.
Add water and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and chill.

title: condensed milk
directions: Place oleo and hot
water
in blender; blend well.
Add milk and sugar.	Blend until smooth and thick.
It works.

title: lite watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients in large bowl.
Tear half the tortillas into three pieces. Dip in chicken mixture.
Place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer half the remaining tortillas, half the chicken mixture and half of both cheeses. Repeat layers.
Spread sour cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except cracker crumbs for sauce.
Add broccoli.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 20 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cheesy crock-pot potatoes
directions: Stir ingredients together, leaving a few onion rings for on top.
Cook in crock-pot covered, 6 hours on low or 4 hours on high.

title: gourmet beef stew
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Remove and set aside.
Add a little olive oil and butter and saute onions.
(You may need to remove some of juice.)
Put meat and juice back into pan.
Add 4 cups water, wine, bouillon cubes, garlic, parsley, bay leaf, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Prepare and add veggies and cook until tender.
Twenty minutes before end of cooking time, add tomatoes.

title: crispy onion chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine butter, worcestershire sauce, mustard, garlic salt, and pepper.
Dip chicken in the butter mixture, then coat with onions.
Place in a greased 9 inch square pan.
Top with any remaining onions.
Drizzle with any remaining butter mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30-35 minutes or until chicken juices run clear.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: monster cookies
directions: Put in a bowl in sequence; mix well.
Drop by ice cream scoops onto an ungreased cookie sheet, allowing room for spreading.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Remove from cookie sheet while still warm.
Makes several dozen.
Recipe may be halved or quartered.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in hot cherry juice.
Add gelatin, softened in the pineapple juice.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until thickened.
Add fruits, nuts and cola.
Combine cream and mayonnaise.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Chill.

title: holly taters
directions: Cut potatoes in wedges and roll in the next 3 ingredients (all mixed together).
Place in a greased baking dish and drizzle squeeze Parkay over them.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Cook pork in large frying pan for 1 or 2 minutes.
Add onion; cook until golden, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Drain seafood in sieve; save liquid.
Add seafood liquid and potatoes to pork mixture.
Cook, covered, until potatoes are thoroughly heated. Mince seafood with knife and add milk and seasonings to pork mixture.
Heat slowly to serving temperature.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir
beef
in 2 tablespoons butter in skillet over low heat
until
brown.
Reserve
1/3 cup bouillon.
Stir remaining bouillon,
ketchup,
garlic
and
salt into skillet. Heat to boiling;
reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender 1 to 1
1/2 hours.
Stir in mushrooms and onion.
Cover and simmer until onion is tender.
Shake reserved bouillon and flour in
tightly
covered container.
Stir into beef mixture. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and stir in sour cream. Toss
noodles
with 1 tablespoon butter and poppy seed.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli.
Mix with bacon, almonds and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over vegetable mixture. (Better if made a day ahead.)

title: easy cheese filled coffee cake
directions: Mix yeast, water and sugar; let stand for 10 minutes.
Add egg, slightly beaten.
Mix flour, salt and cut in margarine.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix and divide into 2 balls.
Roll out each ball into an 8 x 10-inch rectangle using extra flour.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and lemon.
Place filling down the long 1/3 center of dough.
Fold up ends and fold sides over filling.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: grandma tiffany's brown bread
directions: *My grandmother used lard and a table serving spoon as a measure.

title: miniature fruit cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Add to fruit and stir. Pour melted margarine over mixture and stir. Add nuts, egg yolks, sugar and vanilla; pour over mixture and stir. Beat egg whites and fold into mixture. Bake in miniature tins (set on cookie sheet). Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pecans
directions: Cook sugar, buttermilk and salt to soft-ball stage.
Stir in pecans and stir until it almost turns to sugar.
Pour out on waxed paper and separate with fork.
Allow to cool until set.
Store in covered container.

title: frosted treasures
directions: Melt chips for 5 minutes in microwave (High).
Stir and reheat until chocolate is smooth.
Add peanut butter and stir until mixed. Pour over cereal and stir easily until coated.
Pour sugar into a garbage bag and add cereal and shake until coated with sugar. Makes great gifts!

title: fettuccine with salmon and mushrooms
directions: Place a large kettle of salted water over high heat to boil. Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Fresh pasta should cook about 2 minutes; dried pasta should cook about 9 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
In nonstick skillet, heat olive oil and add green onions and mushrooms.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes until onions are tender and lightly browned.
Add garlic and flour and stir to coat vegetables for 1 minute.
Add evaporated skim milk a little at a time, stirring until the sauce begins to simmer and thicken.
Add the juice from the canned salmon and the cream cheese.
Stir until the cheese melts.
Stir in salmon and parsley.
Heat 2 minutes longer.
Divide pasta into 4 portions and top with equal amounts of sauce.
Serve warm with crisp green salad or green vegetable such as broccoli, green beans or zucchini.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tomatoes and basil
directions: Toss all ingredients together and chill for one hour.
Yummy, my favorite.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cut off and scrape corn ears.
Add eggs, sugar, salt and melted butter. Add milk. Bake in 300° oven until firm.

title: old virginia wassail
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a simmer.
Strain and serve hot.

title: squash relish
directions: Lay pecan halves on foil lined pan.
Cover with 3 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle salt to taste.
Put in 300° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn off heat; leave in oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours (doors closed).

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in large Tupperware container.

title: crab melt away
directions: Spread hoagie buns with butter, mayonnaise, mustard and oregano.
Put on sliced ham, salami, Swiss cheese, lettuce, onion and dill pickle.
Wrap in foil and heat until warm through.

title: "guilt free" tomato sauce
directions: Chop first 3 ingredients into bite size pieces.
Place in large, heavy pan, sprayed with cooking spray, and saute about 5 minutes.
Add wine and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer until flavors meld (approximately 20 minutes).
A pinch or 2 of sugar may be added, if too acidic.
Serve over rotini or bow tie pasta.
Sprinkle lightly with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: herbed steak with mustard sauce
directions: Combine mustard, sour cream, vinegar and spices; mix well. Pour 1/2 cup mustard sauce over meat.
Marinate 1/2 hour.
Chill remaining sauce.
Broil or grill over high heat for 20 minutes or until desired doneness.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: chicken and wild rice soup
directions: Prepare rice mix according to package directions (omit butter).
Saute onion, garlic, mushrooms and chicken in oil, 5 to 8 minutes.
Reserve 1/2 cup of broth and add cornstarch; set aside.
Add cooked rice, broth and spices to onion mixture.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Add cornstarch mixture and white wine to soup.
Stir until thickened.
Makes about 11 cups.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Beat together powdered sugar, Cool Whip and oleo.
Stir in pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Pour cherry pie filling on top. Chill and serve.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, bell pepper and onion.
Remove from heat and drain.
In a bowl, mix chicken soup, rice and water.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole dish. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco-cheese animal crackers
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add flour, shredded cheese and butter.
Process until mixture forms a ball, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Wrap dough in heavy-duty plastic wrap; chill 30 minutes.
Unwrap dough and roll to 1/4 inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut with 2 1/2 inch animal-shaped cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned; cool on wire racks.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring cocoa, milk, sugar, margarine and vanilla to a boil and boil exactly 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoon on foil and let cool.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients to make salad (lettuce, shrimp, slivered almonds and oranges).
Use Italian dressing or an oil and vinegar dressing.

title: potato-corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon in soup pot till browned.
Add onion and cook till soft.
Add potatoes and water to cover.
When potatoes are cooked, mash (with potato masher) enough to thicken soup.
Add corn, butter and seasonings and simmer 30 min. Add milk and heat through but do not boil.
Add sour cream and whisk through just before serving.
A can of diced green chilies or minced green peppers may be added.

title: butterscotch pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs slightly; add corn syrup, salt, vanilla, brown sugar and butter.
Mix well; stir in pecans. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 to 35 minutes or until outer edge of filling seems set.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Break 1 bag unsalted large pretzels (use frustration technique!).
Add to Tupperware bowl and shake to coat pretzels. Bake in 250° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, turning once.

title: lemon delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix plain flour, margarine and pecans in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and press to the bottom to form crust. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice and seasonings.
Mix until well blended.
Add crab meat and radishes.
Mix lightly.

title: sweet sour beef 'n' cabbage
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper until meat is browned; drain off fat.
Sprinkle meat mixture with rolled oats, parsley, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Core cabbage; cut into six wedges.
Place atop meat.
In bowl, combine tomato sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and the 1/2 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper; mix well.
Pour over cabbage and meat.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
Drain.
Cool 5 minutes.
Combine sour cream, soup and carrots, then fold in squash and onion.
Combine stuffing and butter.
Put squash mixture in baking dish and cover with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: angel salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Add cream cheese to the hot gelatin mixture.

Measure drained juice from pineapple and fruit cocktail and add water (if necessary) to make 1 1/2 cups. Add this, the marshmallows, pineapple and fruit cocktail to the mixture of gelatin and cream cheese.
Let congeal.
Whip cream or prepare whipped cream substitute according to package directions. Fold into the gelatin-fruit mixture, then add nuts.
Makes a large bowl full of salad.

title: glorified gingerbread
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and salt with hands.
Keep 1/2 cup for the topping.
Mix rest with egg that has been beaten first and add rest of ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer.
Put in pan and put on reserved topping.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch loaf cake pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until springs back at finger touch.

title: latkes
directions: Squeeze shredded potatoes between paper towels to remove the excess moisture.
Combine potatoes and next 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of potato mixture into 1 inch hot oil (325°).
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain well. Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: chili
directions: Slice eggplant.
Dip in beaten egg and roll in flour and Italian bread crumbs.
Brown lightly on both sides in vegetable oil in frypan.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken and onions) and pour over chicken breasts which have been cut in half lengthwise.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove chicken and dust lightly with flour.
Save marinade.
Brown both sides of chicken in butter in large frypan.
Do not overcook, use more butter as needed for browning.
Place in single layer in large casserole. Saute 2 onions, sliced, in 3 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Pour over marinade.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered with foil.
Remove foil; pour 1/4 cup white wine over chicken.
Cook 10 more minutes, uncovered.

title: spanish fruit cake
directions: Mix together water, sugar, nutmeg, Crisco and cinnamon.
Cook 10 or 15 minutes and let cool.

title: pinto bean stew
directions: Pick over beans and wash. Put beans in water and bring to a boil. Put in crock-pot 4 to 8 hours. Lightly cook onion, garlic and meat (if used) and add to beans with tomatoes, chilies and seasonings. Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour to blend flavors. Serve with chili-corn muffins for complete protein without meat.

title: crescent casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 2 long triangles and place in greased 13 x 9-inch glass casserole.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up sides, making sure perforations in dough are sealed. Brown sausage; place in colander and rinse with hot water to remove grease.
Sprinkle sausage on top of dough, then sprinkle cheese on top of sausage.
Add salt and pepper to milk and pour evenly over top of casserole.
Whip eggs and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until eggs are set.
Cut in 8 squares and serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture of sugar, shortening, honey and eggs.
Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: potato noodles
directions: Stir together with fork and add 1 cup flour.
Drop by 1/4 teaspoon in boiling water.
Boil 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse in clear water.
Brown butter and pour over noodles.
Can be mixed with sweet cabbage or cottage cheese or served separate.

title: orange salad
directions: Boil pineapple, sugar and lemon for 3 minutes, then add jello and boiling water.
When it begins to set, add remaining ingredients.

title: pea delight
directions: Blend together peas, tomatoes, butter and mustard.
In separate pan, mix milk and flour well, then add to other ingredients.
Slice eggs on top with bread crumbs and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Pour oil and milk into a measuring cup; do not mix.
Pour all at once into flour.
Stir with a fork until mixture forms a ball.
Lightly knead dough 10 times.
Roll out between sheets of wax paper (if work surface is damp, paper won't slip).
Cut out biscuits with a 2-inch cutter and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 475° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 16 biscuits.

title: veal scallops in marsala wine
directions: Flatten veal cutlets between sheets of plastic wrap with smooth mallet.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.
Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Brown beal on both sides in margarine.
Remove, keep warm.
Stir wine into pan juices.
Mix 1 tablespoon of the flour used for dredging with the bouillon.
Add to skillet.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over cutlets.
Serve with stewed tomatoes, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: roll candy
directions: Work the butter into the powdered sugar. Flatten mixture on a cutting board. Spread peanut butter on it. Then roll it up. Cut into thin slices. Serve.

title: strawberry delight pies
directions: Put strawberries and pecans in a bowl and mix with a fork. Whip cream and fold in milk, lemon juice and strawberry mixture. Pour into two graham cracker pie shells and chill.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream butter; add flour and sugar (confectioners) and mix. Press mixture on bottom of greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes.

title: cabbage soup(lite choice)
directions: In a large saucepan over medium-high heat, bring water to a boil.
Add cabbage and potatoes, carrots, onion, celery, thyme, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add milk and tomato sauce.
Heat over low heat to serving temperature. Remove and discard bay leaf.
Serves 8.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice. Add gelatin and blend well.
Fold cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press 2/3 of cracker mix in bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add filling and sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Chill several hours.

title: stuffed rye boat
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Hollow out rye bread and cut into pieces for dipping.
Fill bread cavity with dip.
Surround bread with pieces of bread and serve.

title: grandma pusey's hot fudge topping
directions: Melt together cocoa and butter.
Add flour and sugar to chocolate as it cooks slowly and stir continuously.
After this is mixed, add canned milk until it is the right consistency.
Cook slowly for a few minutes.

title: pink cloud pie
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and mix thoroughly.
Add ice cubes and stir until all ice is dissolved.
Let chill in refrigerator 10 minutes. Remove and beat whipped cream into jello until smooth. Pour in crust and chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: light as a feather rolls
directions: Crumble yeast in bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon of sugar, scalded milk, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and salt.
Stir to blend and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour gradually and beat with a spoon until smooth.
Turn into greased bowl and let rise until doubled (or let rise in refrigerator overnight).
Punch down and make rolls.
Let rise again and bake dinner rolls in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Add cherry or strawberry pie filling and mix.
Freeze.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cook Eggs.
Cut in halves, remove yolks and mash into a paste adding Ranch Dressing until moist.
Add mixture to egg whites. Garnish with olives or sprinkle paprika on top.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Have cheese and sausage at room temperature.
Mix worcestershire shire, tabasco and sausage.
Add cheese and Bisquick.
Roll into balls and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
May freeze and reheat at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together except potato chips.
Place in baking dish. Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add 3 eggs,
2 jars baby canned plums, 1 cup cooking oil and 1 cup chopped nuts. Mix well.
Grease and lightly flour a tube pan or sheet pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Combine salt and pepper, rub over roast.
Heat oil in a Dutch oven.
Brown roast on all sides.
Add the tomato sauce, water, onions and garlic.
Cover and simmer for 3 - 4 hours or until meat is tender.

title: chicken patties
directions: Mix together grated Fri Chik and onion.
Add spices and egg. Mix well.
Add just enough breading meal to form into patties. Fry patties on medium-low heat until golden brown on both sides. Serve with tartar sauce.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bring to a slow boil.
Reduce and simmer a while.

title: caramel apple bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cube bread.
Toss bread with melted margarine in mixing bowl.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Cut into eighths.
In a square baking pan layer half of apples, cubed bread and caramel sauce. repeat layers.
Bake 25-30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or frozen yogurt if desired.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain well. Add softened margarine and mix.
Add cheese and herbed dressing mix.
Mix well.
Add eggs and mix.
Form into bite-size balls. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until firm.
These may be frozen before baking.
You may need to add more dressing mix if the mixture is difficult to form into balls.

title: egg bake
directions: Put croutons in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix milk, eggs and seasonings and pour over croutons and cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Before baking, you may put meat on top (bacon, sausage, etc.), cut in pieces.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: healthy chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, pineapple, nuts, grapes and celery in a large salad bowl.
Mix together the mayonnaise, sour cream and seasonings.
Stir into the salad mixture and chill an hour. Serve over lettuce.

title: italian cream cake
directions: In large mixing bowl place sugar, margarine (which has been softened to room temperature) and oil.
Beat the sugar mixture until it is fluffy and has a creamy look.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, blending into sugar each time.
Set aside while you beat egg whites, beating until you can form a peak with your spatula.

Blend in the flour with the soda added, alternately with the buttermilk. Mix well, then fold in by hand the coconut, vanilla and egg whites. Pour into three greased and floured 8-inch cake pans or (2) 9-inch pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for thirty (30) minutes or until cakes spring back when slightly pressed on top.
Cool cake layers for 45 minutes before frosting.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Combine in bowl the cake mix, melted margarine and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.

Press 1/2 of cake mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle 1 cup chocolate chips on top. Pour melted caramel mixture on top of chips and mix slightly. Add a small amount of water or milk to remaining cake mixture (until it is spreadable). Spread it evenly on top of caramel mixture.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes. Remove from oven. Let cool and cut into bars at this point. Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes. Store at room temperature.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, slice and soak eggplant in salt water overnight; drain well.
Soak bread crumbs in evaporated milk.
Saute remaining ingredients.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: brownies
directions: Melt the chocolate with the oleo. Add the sugar, eggs, flour and nuts. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pan.
Ice with chocolate icing.

title: porky pie casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onions and green peppers in a heavy skillet. Drain.
Combine eggs and sour cream.
Mix in sausage.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 to 60 minutes or until eggs are firm.
Season to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add egg and beat well. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture alternately with the milk.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from tins at once and roll in melted butter, then in cinnamon sugar mixture.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Combine fruit and yogurt in a bowl.
Add Cool Whip and mix. Pour in crust and freeze.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Spray muffin tins.
Mix all ingredients and spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: josey filled christmas cookies
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter.
Add flour. Gradually chill overnight in refrigerator.
Roll out 1/3-inch thin.
Cut into a triangle.
Place 1/2 teaspoon near center of triangle and then fold the end over like a popover and bake on ungreased cookie tin for 20 minutes at 350°.
Yield depends on size of triangle.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Brush chicken with melted butter.
Put each chicken breast on foil paper.
Mix rest of ingredients and stuff chicken cavities. Seal tightly.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.
Can be served with green bean casserole and salad.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and make into loaf.

title: reese cup cake
directions: Mix together the graham cracker crumbs, margarine, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Press in bottom of loaf pan or glass pan.

title: super nacho dip
directions: Pour taco sauce over the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Rinse and drain well.
Let cool. Chop tomatoes, cucumbers and sliced scallions.
Mix with bottle of Italian dressing and seasoning.
Add spaghetti a little at a time. Mix well and chill for a couple of hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; skin and pick off bones.
Chop up chicken.
Spray Pam in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put stuffing in dish and pour chicken broth over stuffing mix.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: po man's pie
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, melt oleo. In separate bowl,
mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour over melted butter. Do not stir. Then pour in peaches and juice. Put on middle rack. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in casserole dish. Add chicken.
Add soup and 5 cups cold water.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter and press in baking dish.
Mix and beat powdered sugar, eggs and margarine for 15 minutes.
Pour over cracker crust.
Spread with banana slices and pineapple. Then spread with Cool Whip or Dream Whip.
Top with cherries and chopped pecans.
This cake must be refrigerated.

title: lemon angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites with the salt and cream of tartar until stiff. Add 1 cup sugar, a little at a time, continuing to beat until mixture is glossy and sugar is completely dissolved.
Spread into a well buttered 9-inch pie plate, carrying it well out to the rim. Do not get over rim.
Edge should be visible.
Bake in a 275° oven for 25 minutes, then raise heat to 300° and bake 25 minutes more, until a faint brown tinge has appeared.
Remove from oven and let cool completely.

title: beets with pineapple
directions: Combine in saucepan, brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in pineapple tidbits with syrup; cook until thickened.
Add lemon juice and sliced beets.
Cook for about 5 minutes.

title: dieters' salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello.
Add 1 cup juice from oranges and pineapple.
(If there is not enough juice, add water.)
Let set until it begins to thicken.
Add oranges, pineapple and cottage cheese.
Mix thoroughly; place in a mold.
Chill until firm.

title: goo goo bars
directions: Melt oleo, chocolate chips and Eagle Brand milk over low heat. Mix in marshmallows and peanuts.
Drop ball or put into loaf pan and cut into squares.
Good.

title: rice balls
directions: Saute chopped meat, garlic and onion until meat is no longer pink; drain fat. Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper (or garlic powder). Cook 10 to 15 minutes; set aside. Cook rice (use a long grain rice of any "starchie" rice). Add salt and cook until not quite done. Remove from heat and let stand. Add 4 egg yolks, salt, pepper and grated cheese.

title: pizzelles
directions: Mix all ingredients and let rest for 1/2 hour.
Place teaspoonful on hot grill. Thickness of pizzelle depends on how much batter you put on grill.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells 10 to 12 minutes; drain and dry.
Combine cheese with eggs, salt, parsley, oregano and pepper.
Fill shells with 1 or 2 tablespoons of cheese mix.
Spread sauce to cover bottom of pan.
Put the shells in next, then put more sauce to cover the shells.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake at 250° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken that's special
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package until almost done.
Cut each spear across the middle to make it easier to serve.
Place in large flat Pyrex baking dish.
Boil chicken breasts in water until tender.
Bone breasts and cut into pieces and place on top of broccoli.
Combine soup (undiluted), mayonnaise, curry powder, cheese and lemon juice.
Stir over heat until cheese melts.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.
This is just as good with dark meat also.
I use less curry powder and taste as I add it.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Spray pan(s) with nonstick spray. Bake at 350° in layers (two 8 or 9-inch pans) for 20 to 25 minutes or in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes until cake is done. Ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: dino's hot dog chilli
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Then drain grease off. Next, add brown sugar, chili powder, ketchup and a little salt and pepper. Add just enough water to make it a little watery. Place back on stove and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chew-chews
directions: Mix together the shortening, sugar and molasses.
Beat in the eggs very well.
Stir in the remaining ingredients until blended. Line a jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch) with paper, then grease paper well.
Pour in batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Immediately turn onto wire rack.
Remove paper.
Turn right side up and cool.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.
Makes 75 bars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix soup, eggs, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix with broccoli.
Place in greased baking dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onions.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook uncovered for 5 hours on low heat.
Add water as desired.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Add oleo and stir to melt.
Stir in sugar, brown sugar and eggs. Beat to blend.
Add flour, soda, cocoa, salt and 1/2 of chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rest of chips on the top and 2 to 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet.
Add all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Line baking dish with chips.
Layer meat, cheese and chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: steven's special sour sauce
directions: Beat eggs, salt and mustard.
Add vinegar and blend in milk. Great over mashed potatoes.

title: dump cake
directions: Melt 1/2 stick oleo in 11 x 13 dish. Pour fruit and juice in dish and mix. Take box of cake mix and pour over fruit mixture, dry. Cut slices of oleo (1 1/4 sticks) over cake mix. Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: strike buster
directions: Serve chilled and up in martini glass.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugars and flour. Beat in thoroughly the eggs, vanilla, milk and butter. Fold in nuts (optional). Pour into pastry-lined pie pan. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until just set.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix both boxes jello with the hot water and then the cold water.
Add remaining ingredients (except pineapple juice) and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Put in bowl in layers - carrots, onions, peppers.

title: grilled marinated turkey breast
directions: Mix marinade ingredients in large bowl or heavy plastic bag. Marinate, turning several times, at least 2 hours at room temperature or up to 1 day in refrigerator.
Remove turkey; discard marinade.

title: family reunion cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and onions.
Boil remaining ingredients.
Pour boiled mixture over cabbage and onions; refrigerate overnight.

title: colorful fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss gently.
Cover and chill. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: microwave hot cocoa
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and hot water in 1-quart microwave-proof measuring cup.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until boiling.
Add milk; stir and microwave an additional 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until hot.
Stir in vanilla and blend well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: white bread
directions: Add together the yeast mixture, water, sugar, salt and shortening; add 5 cups flour to make dough pasty.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover; raise until double.
Punch dough down and raise again.
Make loaf and place seam down.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes (should sound hollow when done).

title: gayle's potato soup
directions: Cube potatoes and cook in broth till tender.
Fry bacon crisp while potatoes are cooking.
Pour off most of bacon fat from pan, and cook onions till tender with the bacon.
When potatoes are tender; add bacon and onions and butter, salt and pepper to taste. Thicken soup with flour and water paste.
Simmer for 5 minutes till slightly thickened.
Add milk and sour cream mixture.
Stir in chopped parsley.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix butter and Crisco. Cream well. Add cocoa to sugar and cream with shortening. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each one. Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Add with milk. Bake in tube pan in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut scotch crunchies
directions: Melt Candi-Quik and peanut butter.
Combine marshmallows, Krispies, nuts and noodles in a large mixing bowl.
Pour Candi-Quik mixture over this; stir to combine.
Spread in 9-inch square on foil or waxed paper.
Cut into squares.
Yields 36 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: 40 mile bean salad
directions: Stir together beans and the corn.
In small bowl, with wire whisk or fork, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over bean mixture; toss lightly, being careful not to break apart beans. Chill at least 2 hours.
Remove and discard garlic before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat until soft, butter or Crisco.
Add gradually and blend until creamy the 1/2 cup brown sugar and the 1/2 cup sugar; beat in the egg, peanut butter, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Add the flour.
Roll the dough into small balls. Place them on a greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with a fork. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: tina's cheese ball
directions: Place cheeses in small mixing bowl; let stand until softened. Add onion and Worcestershire sauce; blend on low speed.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy, scraping sides and bottom of bowl. Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Shape mixture into 1 large ball or into 30 to 36 (1-inch) balls.
Roll in parsley and place on serving plate.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Arrange crackers around large ball and serve as a spread.
To serve small balls, insert a toothpick in each and serve with crackers.

title: new york venders' sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic until clear.
Add marinara sauce and paprika; simmer for 10 minutes.
Place hot dog on a bun; put sauce over dog and add a little kraut.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large microwave-safe bowl. Mix together well.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Mix together well. Place in microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir well.
Repeat in 3 minute intervals until thick (usually 2 more times).
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix until butter is melted.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Spread meringue over hot filling, sealing to edge of pastry.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 28 minutes.

title: baked ziti
directions: In Dutch oven or large kettle, prepare ziti as package directs; drain and set aside.
In same Dutch oven, over medium-high heat, cook ground beef until well browned, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove Dutch oven from heat; stir in Ricotta, next 5 ingredients and half of sauce until well mixed.
Add ziti and toss gently to coat well. Spoon mixture into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour remaining sauce evenly over ziti mixture; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: easy microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips and condensed milk in glass bowl. Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread in waxed paper lined 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Stir all together.
Roll in 1 1/2 cups of pecans.
Chill.

title: chocolate refrigerator cake
directions: Line loaf pan with wax paper.
Place 8 halves of ladyfingers in bottom of pan.
Melt chocolate over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating vigorously after each egg.
Beat egg whites stiff; fold in and add vanilla.
Whip half of cream, fold in and spread.
Spread chocolate on ladyfingers in 4 rows.
Top with ladyfingers, chill at least 4 hours.
Frost with whipped cream.

title: angel food orange sherbet delight
directions: Mix the gelatin with the boiling water.
When it is just cool, add sherbet, then add the topping mix, prepared according to directions.
Add oranges (drained) and pineapple (drained).
Cut cake in cubes.

title: helen heath's sweet hamburger relish
directions: Put
tomatoes,
peppers and onions through course blade of chopper
or food processor.
Put in preserving kettle.
Add 1 cup of
water.
Simmer
gently for 15 minutes.
Drain well, pressing out
all
liquid.
Add
vinegar,
brown sugar, salt, curry powder and celery seed.
Bring to a boil. Simmer gently for 5 minutes. Pour into sterile jars.
Seal.

title: easy cornbread muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Add flour with salt and baking powder.
Add corn meal, stirring only enough to mix.
Fill greased hot muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in oil until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes and next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon cold water and stir into the sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture bubbles.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover and simmer until done, about 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Add the Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Start layers with the wafers, bananas and then pudding mix.
Keep repeating until large bowl is full.
Keep refrigerated.
Recipe is good for several days.

title: honey puffs
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain and serve with diluted honey and cinnamon. Serve warm.

title: ground turkey and vegetables
directions: Lightly brown ground turkey in large frypan (no oil necessary).
When turkey is browned, add frozen vegetables.
Cover pan.
Cook five minutes.
Stir.
Cover again for another five minutes.
If you wish, sprinkle soy sauce over turkey and vegetables.
Ready to serve.
May be enjoyed alone or served over steamed rice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted margarine.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and set aside.
Beat sugar, eggs, vanilla and 2 sticks softened margarine about 10 to 15 minutes until fluffy and thick with electric mixer.
