Spread evenly over crumbs; layer bananas and pineapple evenly and cherries also. Cover with Cool Whip; garnish with nuts and cherries.
Cover and chill overnight (Saran Wrap).
Makes 12 (3-inch) squares.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and salad dressing mix in medium bowl until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients, cover. Refrigerate several hours until well chilled.

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Mash pimento in oil from can.
Mash softened cheese.
Mix well together.
Add sugar to sweeten to taste.
Add enough mayonnaise to make spreading consistency.
May add pickle relish, if desired.

title: delda's dip
directions: Brown the 2 meats and drain off grease.
In a separate bowl, melt the Velveeta cheese in microwave (don't overcook).
Combine meats, Ro-Tel tomatoes, chilies and mushroom soup in crock-pot. Set crock-pot on low just to keep the dip warm.
Add warm cheese. Stir good and now you are ready to enjoy.
Fantastic with King size Fritos or your favorite chips and crackers.
Great for a fun family get together.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Purchase 6 firm tomatoes.
Cut tomatoes in half.
Scoop out pulp of tomatoes.
Save pulp for further use. Fill tomatoes with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon olive oil on each tomato.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread out in a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all together, making sure all liquid is used. If not, add more cracker crumbs. Form into about 5 or 6 patties. Fry in oil slowly until browned on both sides.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add dry Jiffy mix.
Stir well. Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix together wafer crumbs, pecans, powdered sugar and cocoa. Blend bourbon and syrup.
Combine the mixtures.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll lightly in powdered sugar and refrigerate in airtight container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sharon's macaroni and hamburger dish
directions: Mix all ingredients, except green olives, with browned ground beef and onion.
Simmer for at least an hour.
Just before serving, stir in green olives and simmer another 15 minutes.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Top with cheese and melt.

title: fast turkey a la king
directions: In a saucepan, cook the chopped onion and peas in the chicken broth until tender.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the noodles.
Cook the noodles according to the package directions. Drain.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine in saucepan cornstarch, sugar and water.
Cook until clear and thick.
Add Jell-O and cool.
Pour over fresh strawberries.
Top with whipped cream.
Refrigerate to keep firm. Can also use fresh sliced peaches and peach Jell-O or fresh raspberries and raspberry Jell-O.

title: 15 bean soup
directions: Wash bean mix thoroughly; place in pot and cover with water and 2 tablespoons salt.
Soak overnight.
In the morning, drain and add 2 quarts water.
Add ham, ham hock or sausage.
Bring to boil.
Simmer slowly for 2 1/2 hours.
Add onion, tomatoes, chili powder, lemon juice, garlic and salt and pepper.
Simmer slowly 30 minutes.
A can of stewed tomatoes can be added instead of regular tomatoes (adds a special taste).
Serve with salad and crackers or corn bread.
Better the second day!

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven of 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn heat down to 300° and cook until done.

title: hash browns potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large casserole dish that has been sprayed well with Pam.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: krispie scotcheroos
directions: Melt Karo syrup until bubbling.
Mix with sugar.
Add peanut butter.
Quickly add Rice Krispies.
Mix together in large bowl. Pack into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt together butterscotch and chocolate chips.
Spread over Rice Krispies.

title: trader vic's salad
directions: Mix all together and toss with dressing.

title: cocoa peanut butter dreams
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Blend in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by teaspoon or tablespoon on wax paper.
Let set at room temperature 10 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine
evaporated
milk, sugar and butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove
from heat and stir in marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir
vigorously for about 1 minute (until well blended).
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill before cutting.

title: chicken soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in stockpot and heat over medium heat.

title: oven barbecue ribs
directions: Cover spareribs with the sauce.
Let stand 2 hours.
In 375° oven on large rack, set ribs right side up.
Keep brushing with sauce until done.
(Put 1/2-inch water into roasting pan holding rack of ribs.)
Bake 45 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel onions.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices and separate into rings.
Set aside.
Combine flour and next 6 ingredients.
Beat with a wire whisk until mixture is smooth.
Pour oil to a depth of 2 to 3 inches into a Dutch oven or heavy saucepan; heat to 375°. Dip onion rings in batter.
Fry, turning once, until golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown beef, celery and onions.
Add rest of ingredients.
Top with more noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: philip's sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add sugar and eggs. Stir in vanilla, then mix in flour, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda. Roll cookie dough into small balls and flatten with a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine shortening, brown sugar and flour with pastry blender and remove scant cup.
Blend together buttermilk mixture, egg and vanilla.
Sprinkle cup of crumbs over cake.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, spices and eggs.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Pour into well-greased custard cups. Set in pan of warm water.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until an inserted knife comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham and corn skillet
directions: Brown ham in butter.
Add corn, seasoning and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until eggs are set.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Bring to a boil pineapple, sugar, water and gelatine.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator to gel overnight.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugars just to a boil.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Stir in peanuts and cereal.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.
Use plenty of crushed ice. Makes 20 cups.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large deep casserole dish.
Lay bacon on top and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: what-cha-call-it casserole
directions: Brown ground meat in a skillet with the onions.
In a saucepan combine the chili peppers, soups, milk and tomatoes; then bring to a boil, set aside.
Tear the tortillas up and put a layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer the meat soup mixture and tortillas until all gone.
Top with the cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: morsonian cream delight
directions: Cut 1/2 gallon of ice cream into 2 portions.
Generously cover with 1/2 container of Cool Whip each.
Consume with large spoon. Serves 2.

title: fine noodle pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well; add cottage cheese, cream cheese and margarine.
Beat in sour cream, add vanilla and add noodles.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Pour on milk and mix slightly.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes, reduce oven heat to 350° and bake for 1 hour.

title: ritz squash casserole
directions: Mix together the margarine and cracker crumbs, saving half for topping.
Mix all ingredients; pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: italian spaghetti delight
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add seasonings.
Add tomato soup and simmer.
Adjust seasonings and add cheese.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add softened butter and cream together.
Add beaten eggs slowly.
Sift flour and salt together and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Turn onto a floured board and knead for 1/2 minute. The dough should be soft.
Make into little balls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Roll out each ball on floured board with the palm of hand to form strip about 4 1/2 to 5-inches long. Intertwine 2 strips and shape into a circle, tucking end on the bottom.
Place on a greased cookie sheet; cover and let rise in warm place, free of draft.
When doubled, bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until tops are slightly golden.
Yield:
about 2 dozen rolls.

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Mix together warm water, yeast and sugar.
When yeast dissolves, add salad oil, buttermilk and soda and mix well.
Add self-rising flour.
Pour in a covered bowl for a few hours or overnight.
Stir slightly and dip out with a spoon onto a floured board.
Work with hands to form a biscuit.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remaining dough can be kept covered in refrigerator for a week.

title: crisco yellow cake(9-inch)
directions: Blend thoroughly the first 6 ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Next, add the eggs, milk and vanilla. Beat 2 more minutes. Pour into greased cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cake will bake higher if put at top of oven. After you take layers out, cover with tinfoil to hold in moisture while cooling. Don't leave in pans longer than 15 minutes.

title: clinton's chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda on waxed paper.
Beat together shortening, sugars, and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer until creamy.
Add eggs, beating until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture and rolled oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool on sheets on wire rack for 2 minutes.
Remove from sheet and cool on wire rack.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the frosted flakes and 1/2 stick margarine. Melt margarine; stir in frosted flakes and place on top of potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered, in 11 x 14-inch pan.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: In a large saucepan bring water to boil.
Lower heat.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add marshmallows and cream cheese that has been cut into small pieces.
Stir until melted. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into ungreased mold and chill until firm.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes until tender.
Drain water and pour into baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over potatoes. Bake at 325° until candied about 30 minutes.

title: macaroni-cheese salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and cool.
Cut cheese into small cubes. Dice eggs.
Mix with peas, celery and onions.
Add mayonnaise and mustard.
Toss all ingredients with macaroni, seasoned to taste. Chill and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: pinto fiesta cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add mashed beans.
Sift dry ingredients together and add slowly to butter mixture.
Fold in apples, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; fold in grated cheese.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay package of rolls flat on a cookie sheet. Bake until slightly brown. Mix cream cheese, mayo, sour cream and seasonings together. Spread on cooled crust. Add vegetables on top.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak and dry ingredients together.
After browning, add soup; simmer 20 minutes.
Add sour cream; simmer 10 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in bowl with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Let cool, then add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Mix all other ingredients with jello.
Pour in bowl and let jell.

title: quick creamy dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Serve with chips or crackers. Yields 1 cup.

title: angel biscuits #2
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water; set aside. Measure and
sift dry ingredients together.
Cut shortening into mixture.
Add milk and yeast; stir until well blended.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into biscuits, using 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place rolls in greased pan and let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Brush top with butter or margarine.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In large heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt.
Stir constantly over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until syrup reaches 300° on candy thermometer (hard crack stage).
Stir in peanuts.
Mix soda and vanilla and quickly stir into candy. Mixture will foam.
Quickly turn out into greased 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers up to four weeks.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form a loaf.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Spread ketchup on top for nice sweet taste. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ron bushyager's chocolate chip pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine in large bowl the first 6 ingredients.
Blend well.
Stir flour into mixture.
Press dough evenly over bottom of a 12 to 14-inch pizza pan; form rim along edge.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Continue to bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until marshmallows are puffy and light brown.
Cool.
Cut into wedges. Store in tightly covered container.
This was a big hit as a rehearsel treat!

title: spiced tea
directions: Substitute raisins and/or chopped dates for sugar in applesauce, cookies and even apple pie!
It works great; just experiment.

title: toasted pecan clusters
directions: Melt butter in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread pecans evenly in pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Place candy coating in top of a double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until coating melts. Cool 2 minutes.
Add pecans and stir until coated.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool completely.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese.
Soften cheese and blend together.
Add Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and onion.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and cut in small pieces.
Add mayonnaise and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put mixture into ovenproof dish and heat in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.
You may substitute 8 ounce package cream cheese for mayonnaise.

title: supper popover
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown ground beef in skillet; drain. Stir in tomato sauce, green pepper, 2 tablespoons flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, the pepper and parsley flakes.
Heat to boiling, boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, sprinkle cheese on top.

title: fresh raspberry pie filling
directions: Stir sugar, cornstarch, salt and raspberries and place in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: nash's jalapeno "oilfield" cornbread
directions: First, make pastry for a 2-crust pie and prepare 9-inch pastry lined pan and pastry topping.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Blend 3 cups of the orange juice with all other ingredients in blender.
Pour into pitcher and add the remaining 3 cups of orange juice.
Stir and serve.
Makes 7 cups.

title: cheese pepper bread
directions: Grease 2 one pound coffee cans.
Dissolve yeast in hot water; add 1 1/3 cups flour, sugar, salt, soda, sour cream and egg. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed.
Beat 2 minutes on high.
Stir in rest of flour, cheese and pepper.
Split batter; put in warm place.
Let rise for about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour; brown in margarine.
Remove chicken. Stir soup, seasonings and water into drippings.
Cook and stir to a boil.
Spread Minute rice (uncooked) in a 1 3/4-quart greased casserole dish.
Pour all but 1/3 cup soup mixture over rice. Stir to moisten.
Top with chicken and rest of soup mixture. Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender. Serves 6 to 8.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix meats, onion, parsley, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Soak bread crumbs in cream for 5 minutes, then mix all together. Shape into small balls.
Make your gravy; melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet with drippings from meatballs and 2 tablespoons flour.
Add 1 beef bouillon cube.
Dissolve in 1 1/4 cup boiling water and 1 teaspoon gravy mate.
Cook and stir until thickened. Put meatballs into gravy and cook slowly 30 minutes.
Baste often. Makes 40.

title: italian soup
directions: Saute sausage, dried onions and green pepper together until sausage is cooked.
Drain off grease.
Combine rest of ingredients, except paste.
Add the sausage, onions and green pepper mixture. Simmer for 1 hour.
Add pasta and continue cooking until pasta is done.
Serve with French bread.
Yields 8 bowls.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soups, onion, green chilies and dash of salt.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with tortillas dipped in oil.
Layer with chicken pieces, soup and cheese.
Repeat layers, beginning with tortillas. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and cabbage stir-fry
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper and drain.
Stir in tomatoes, ketchup, sugar and cole slaw mix.
Cook 5 minutes until done.
Serve over rice.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Put in measuring cup the warm water, yeast and sugar; set aside.
Put into large mixing bowl the sugar, salt, peanut oil or corn oil, beaten eggs and water; mix well.
Then add yeast mixture.
Mix in enough all-purpose flour (about 8 cups) to keep from being sticky.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Knead down and make off rolls as desired.
Let rise 2 hours or longer.
Bake at 400° until light brown.
Store remaining dough in refrigerator.
Will keep 3 or 4 days.
May roll out on floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Use melted butter on one side and fold over for Parkerhouse rolls.

title: chili beans
directions: In large skillet cook hamburger meat, onion and bell pepper until meat is done.
Drain grease, then add tomatoes, ketchup, beans, salt and pepper.
Simmer for at least 20 minutes.

title: chicken breast in wine
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper to taste. Brown slowly in butter or oleo. Remove and place in covered baking dish.
Chop onion and brown in butter remaining in skillet. Add flour and mix well. Add mushrooms and juice, then wine.
Pour over chicken and cook at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, combine 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stir in egg yolks.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in next 3 ingredients. Spoon hot filling into pie shell.
In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1/3 cup sugar.
Continue baking until stiff peaks form.
Spread over pie filling.

title: maryland gingerbread
directions: Add beaten eggs to sugar, molasses and melted shortening.
Add flour, sifted with other dry ingredients.
Add hot water.
Bake in greased pan about 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve warm with Victory Sauce and whipped cream.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Pour into pan with a spoon.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: danish coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Put shortening, sugar, salt and flour in large bowl.
Mix as for pie crust.
Beat egg yolks, milk and yeast mixture.
Add to flour and beat well.
Divide into 4 parts and roll thin, about 11 inches long and 10 inches wide. Spread butter, brown sugar, nuts and almond paste onto the rolled out crust.
Fold both sides over and let rise until light.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and lay flat on 13 x 9 cookie sheet. Bake as directed. Spread refried beans while rolls are still warm, then allow to cool. Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Spread over beans. Top with diced tomatoes, onions and cheese. Chill for 1 hour. Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: raspberry-applesauce jello mold
directions: Heat applesauce over medium heat in a heavy saucepan, stirring constantly, so that it will not burn.
When it is bubbling, remove from heat and stir in the Jell-O, mixing well.
Stir in the thawed raspberries.
Pour this mixture into an oiled mild and refrigerate until sets.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix the first three ingredients in a bowl.
Mix the dressing of sour cream and other ingredients until smooth.
Pour over fruit and nuts and place in refrigerator until
ready to serve.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix together.
Add 5 tbsp. to 8 oz. hot water to make hot cocoa.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat good.
Flour raisins and nuts in a little of the flour.
Add the rest of the flour with milk.
Add nutmeg, then raisins and pecans.
Bake in 350° oven in 3 layers.

title: pineapple ice
directions: Boil 2 cups of water with the sugar for 5 minutes.
Remove from the heat and stir in the pineapple, lemon juice and salt. Cool.
Pour into ice cube trays and freeze.

title: swiss cheese casserole bread
directions: Heat sour cream over low heat just until lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixer bowl. Add sour cream, sugar, shortening, salt, and 2 cups of the flour. Blend 30 seconds on low speed, scraping bowl constantly. Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally (or beat by hand 300 strokes). Stir in remaining flour and the cheese until smooth. Scrape batter from side of bowl. Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 45 minutes.

title: easy coconut custard pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake
for
minutes
at	350° or until crust is brown and custard is firm.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat until done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20-30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake made with cake mix
directions: In a medium size bowl, combine cake mix, oil, eggs, buttermilk, cocoa and food coloring.
Bake according to package instructions.
This quick version is rather like a pound cake.

title: petite cheesecake cookies
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice, and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Drop one vanilla wafer into the bottom of each cupcake liner.
Fill cups 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until set.
Top with your favorite fruit topping.

title: chicken and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients. Mix together well. Bake in a covered baking dish. Bake, covered, 35 to 45 minutes. Remove cover; bake 10 to 15 minutes longer. Serve immediately.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Next combine butter, vanilla, cocoa, Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Pour over cake.
Cool and serve.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, spoon batter into greased muffin tins.
Do not allow to rise before baking.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Will keep for several days in refrigerator.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: easy meal
directions: Cook onion and garlic in olive oil. Add tomatoes, corned beef and bay leaf. Simmer 30 minutes or longer. Take out bay leaves. Serve on toast or rice.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Mix crackers and butter; spread evenly on bottom and sides of greased spring-form cake pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix gelatin and water.
Cool, then chill until slightly thickened.
Beat cold gelatin until foamy.
Add berries. Continue beating.
Add a spoonful of softened ice cream at a time. Beat until double in volume.
Pour in pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours. Slice and garnish with whipped cream and berries.

title: tea punch
directions: Brew tea.
Mix other ingredients (you may add other juices such as peach, pear, pineapple or apricot; remember to cut down the amount of sugar when adding these sweetened juices).
Makes 1 gallon unless other juices are added.

title: strawberry-rhubarb-pineapple jam
directions: In big pan, mix rhubarb, drained pineapple and sugar.
Let set 30 minutes.
Bring slowly to a boil and cook for 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add strawberry jello. Stir until dissolved.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and top with melted paraffin.
Label and store.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard and honey.
Place chicken on a greased grill over medium heat.
Brush with half of salad dressing mixture.
Grill for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining salad dressing mixture.
Continue grilling for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: chocolate crack-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and stir in cocoa; blend well, then cool.
Add the sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread pie filling in a baking dish.
In a bowl, add flour, oats, brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Mix well with hands. Sprinkle on top of pie filling.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: aunt clara's homemade chili
directions: Put meat into pan and brown. Drain off excess fat. Add all the remaining ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Melt 2 sticks
of
oleo
in a large pan.
Add the brown sugar and
white sugar.
Mix thoroughly.	Add oatmeal and mix. Pat this into a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Melt
chocolate
chips
over
low
heat.
Mix
in peanut butter. Spread this over the bars.	Enjoy!

title: strawberry torte
directions: Mix well.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: curried rice
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Add tomatoes and curry powder; cook for 5 minutes.
Bring water to boil.
Add salt, then the curried mixture.
Sprinkle in rice.
Cover with a tight fitting lid; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chicken rice-a-roni
directions: Mix all ingredients well, put into greased heavy casserole dish and bake at 350 F for one hour.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients while potatoes are partially frozen.
Put into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine and mix with 1/3 cup crushed cornflakes.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: borsch(beet soup)
directions: Simmer consomme or stock in open pot with the cabbage leaf. Add more water, if necessary. Also, cook onion and peppercorns in the stock. Strain and keep hot.
Peel beets and cut into matchstick pieces or coarsely grate.
Set aside 1 heaping tablespoonful of the beets mixed with 3 tablespoons water; this is for color.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper in a large pot. Then add tomato sauce, chili beans, chili powder, salt & pepper and the jalapenos on medium heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place half the slices in a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with half the lemon juice.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle half over apples,
Repeat layers, ending with sugar flour mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Increase temperature to 400° and bake 10 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and store in jars.
Use 1 tablespoon in cup of hot water.

title: filled puff shells
directions: In saucepan, bring beer to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add butter and stir until melted.
With a wooden spoon, stir in flour and salt all at once.
Cook, stirring, until mixture forms into a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition until smooth.
Stir in cheese, if used.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered baking sheet, swirling top of each (allow room for expansion).
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 10 minutes more or until lightly browned.
Cool on racks.
Split and fill puffs with your favorite egg, ham, tuna or chicken salad.
Makes 24 puffs.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill.
Form small balls and bake at 350° on a cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tomato happiness soup
directions: Blend well with rotary beater soup, cream, lemon juice and Tabasco.
Mix with cottage cheese and onions.
Chill.
Sprinkle with chives to serve. Makes 6 portions.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook onions and garlic in fat until soft, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Stir once or twice.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach, water chestnuts and onions.
Cover and chill 2 hours. Stir before serving.
Serve in hollowed out bread with bread pieces or crackers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix the soups, sour cream and chiles together.
Layer 1/2 sour cream mixture, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 tortillas and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.
Also, better if made the day before serving.

title: french onion soup casserole
directions: Place meat on top of other ingredients.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar together.
Add melted oleo.
Roll in balls and refrigerate for several hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all the ingredients; best mixed with your hands. Forms into ball.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Cover and chill. Serve with Bacon Thins or Wheat Thins.
Good made the day before serving.

title: old-fashion sugar cookies
directions: Combine granulated sugar, confectioners sugar, margarine and oil together.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and soda and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Roll into balls size of walnuts.
Roll in granulated sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Remove the pits from dates by slashing one side of date. Place nut in date and squeeze date closed.
Roll stuffed date in granulated sugar.

title: favorite waffles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine milk and egg yolks; stir in dry ingredients.
Add oil or melted shortening and stir. Fold in egg whites, leaving a few little fluffs-- do not over mix. Bake in preheated waffle iron.
Makes 8 waffles.

title: gwen's meat balls
directions: Combine ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly by hand.
Pinch off small sections; roll into a ball.
Place meat balls on baking sheet and bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 15 minutes.
Drain after removing from oven.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine with chocolate in saucepan on low heat setting on an electric range. Remove from heat. Add all ingredients, except eggs and blend well. Add eggs and beat thoroughly. Pour in a greased 9 x 9 pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Cool and cut into small squares.

title: jibby's breakfast bundt cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Then combine nuts, 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle this over top of batter and marble in with knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly on rack.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla, butter extract and milk and pour over cake.
This is great for any occasion!

title: date cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate rocky road cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch Bundt pan.
In large bowl, blend packet of cake mix and next 3 ingredients until moistened.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in 1/2 cup marshmallows, 1/4 cup chocolate pieces and 1/4 cup nuts.
Pour into greased pan and top with remaining marshmallows, chocolate pieces and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake in pan on cooling rack.
Blend packet of glaze mix (number 2) with 1 2/3 tablespoons warm water. Drizzle over the cooled cake.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Rub margarine over the sides and bottom of heavy 6-quart saucepan.
Add sugar and cream and remaining margarine.
Bring to a boil and cook until 235°.
Remove pan from heat.
Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla flavoring.
Beat until glossy.
Spread quickly in a greased cake pan.
Let cool. Cut into squares.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and seasoning with butter and onion.
Add milk to bouillon and gradually add to flour mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add crab meat; heat.
Garnish with parsley sprinkled over top if desired.
Serves 6.

title: broiled valentine sandwich
directions: Place bread on broiler pan.
Center heart pattern on bread. Generously sprinkle Parmesan cheese evenly on bread not covered by heart pattern.
Lift edge of heart pattern with table knife and carefully remove.
Bake under broiler until golden brown.
Yield: 1.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place Tater Tots in large deep dish cake pan.
Heat Tater Tots until warm.

title: mint julep shake
directions: Combine ice cream and milk in a blender and whirl until smooth.
Add Oreo* bulk cookie pieces (large crunch) and blend until smooth.
Pour into a 16 ounce glass and garnish with whipped topping and and Oreo* chocolate sandwich cookie.

title: company-style sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, remove seeds and slice lengthwise.
Soak for 24 hours in lime water (2 cups fresh lime to 2 gallons water). Remove and rinse well through several changes of cold water to remove lime sediment.
Cover pickles with ice water and let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Dissolve sugar and salt in vinegar; add spice bag and bring to a boil.
Pour hot syrup over pickles and let set overnight.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain. Add all vegetables listed and any leftover veggies to hamburger meat. Add diced potatoes and cook on low until done.

title: pineapple pecan pie
directions: Cream thoroughly first five ingredients.
Blend in egg yolks and corn syrup.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Gently fold in well beaten egg whites.
Turn into pie shell and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Prepare at least 1 hour before using.
Shake all ingredients together in a covered jar until blended.
Shake several times during the hour.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: "seven-up cake"
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together. Add eggs and beat. Add flour alternately with extracts and 7-Up. Pour into a large greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: sausage fondue bake
directions: Layer bread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put thoroughly cooked sausage on bread. Sprinkle on cheese.
Beat together milk, eggs and dry mustard.
Pour over other ingredients. Dilute soup with the 1/2 cup milk and pour this over top. Refrigerate overnight or at least 3 hours.
Bake 1 hour at 300°, uncovered. Serves 6 to 8.
Great for breakfast or brunch.

title: banana cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Stir in bananas, buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt. Add pecans.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto Pam sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in water until tender.
In a deep dish, layer carrots and onions.

title: cauliflower and carrot casserole
directions: Cook the carrots and cauliflower in boiling water 10 minutes; drain.
Place vegetables in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Combine soup and milk, stirring well.
Pour over vegetables. Combine cracker crumbs and butter, mixing well. Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: moroccan chicken(4 to 6 servings)
directions: In 3-quart casserole, place chicken with meaty portions along outside of dish.
Add onions and carrots.
Combine broth, lemon juice, lemon rind, paprika, ginger, turmeric and cinnamon.
Pour over chicken; cover.
Microwave at High power 22 to 27 minutes, until chicken is done and vegetables are tender; rotate dish 1/2 turn after 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cream of cheese frill cookies
directions: Beat butter and vanilla until creamy.
Add flour, salt and oats; mix until well blended.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Chill thoroughly.

title: little debbie's pork barbecue
directions: After roasting pork, put broth to the side to cool.
Shred cooled pork into crock-pot or baking dish.
(Remove grease from broth, using about a tray of ice cubes.
Grease will stick to ice cubes after broth is cooled.
Throw ice cubes and fat away.)
Add 1/2 of broth to shredded pork, brown sugar and catsup.
Mix well and taste (add more sugar or catsup to your taste).
Let simmer in oven or crock-pot (simmer at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes).
Serve over rolls.

title: reese cups
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Line molds with chocolate.
Cool.
Mix peanut butter, oleo and powdered sugar until smooth.
Put in chocolate cups.
Cover with chocolate.

title: monkey bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, margarine, salt, soda, vanilla and egg. Beat at medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add oats, peanut butter and coconut.
Spread dough in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan with hands. Sprinkle top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in preheated 375° oven or until edges are golden and center stays soft.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt margarine and mix with cocoa.
In a bowl, beat 2 eggs and add sugar, flour, salt and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Add chocolate mixture and blend.
Add nuts.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Chocolate chips make brownies more moist.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Divide strawberries into two piles.
Slice one pile in half. Crush remaining berries with fork.
Put the crushed berries in a heavy-bottom pan and stir in the cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture looks clear and is thickened.
Remove from heat and cool.
Gently stir in the sliced berries.
Put the strawberry mixture into the baked crust.
Just before serving, whip the cream with powdered sugar and spread over pie.

title: chewy chews
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter.
Mix in other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on foil or waxed paper.
Wait until they harden.

title: carrots and bacon
directions: Pray.
Wash carrots and cook with skins on.
Cut bacon into bite-sized pieces and fry until crisp.
Remove bacon and simmer onions until soft in bacon drippings.
Peel carrots and slice. Add to onions and simmer until heated.
Add bacon.

title: cranberry cream cheese log
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together.
Fold in the pineapple and banana.
Whip the heavy cream until it forms peaks and slowly fold in mixture.
Fold in cranberry sauce chunks.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Trim fat from meat.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven, brown meat in hot oil.
Drain off fat.
Add water, bouillon granules, oregano, basil, bay leaves, garlic and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Add carrots, onions and potatoes. Spoon juices over vegetables.
Simmer, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes and continue to simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: chopped chicken liver
directions: Chop onions.
Saute 1 1/2 onions and chicken livers in 2 tablespoons of oil over low heat until livers are thoroughly cooked and crumble easily and onions are brown, but not burned.

title: cream cheese croissants
directions: Unroll crescent rolls, separating into 8 triangles.
Gently spread 1 1/2 teaspoons of cream cheese on top of each triangle. Roll up each triangle, beginning at the wide end.
Place rolls, point side down, on baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 11 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: classic deviled eggs
directions: Slice the eggs in half, and carefully remove the yolks into a small mixing bowl. Mash the yolks with a fork. Stir in the mayonnaise, mustard, sweet relish and salt, and mix until creamy. Spoon the mixture into the hollows in the egg whites. Sprinkle with a little paprika for color if desired. May double or triple this recipe.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat.
Add 1/3 can milk stir until well blended.
Slowly stir in remaining milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, fold in vanilla and pour into pie shell.
Cool.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Cut halibut into 1-inch squares.

Put water, crab boil and sugar in a Dutch oven. Bring to a slow boil. Drop squares of halibut, 12 pieces at a time, into water. Cook until it floats, about 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from water and put in a bowl.
Now in small (custard cups) cups put melted butter in and serve while hot.
(Dunk halibut in butter.)
Makes 2 servings.

title: mushroom lasagna
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and soup.
Cover bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan with sauce.
Alternate layers of noodles, hamburger, cheese and sauce.
Spread sauce over top.
Mozzarella cheese may be placed over all if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Delicious.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat. Add spaghetti sauce, corn and onion. In a casserole dish, place Tater Tots in single rows to fill the whole bottom of the dish.
Cover with meat mixture. Sprinkle on cheese.
Cook at 375° until cheese is melted, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: okra gumbo freezer mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in two 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans. Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours or until okra is tender, stirring once after 1 hour.
Cool completely.
Spoon mixture into 1-pint freezer containers.
Label and freeze.
Yield: about 6 pints.

title: microwave chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining chips.
Microwave on High (10) for 5 to 7 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes, until done.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Melt butter; stir in the flour and add salt, pepper and milk and cook until thick.
Add all Velveeta except 2 slices.
Mix in the macaroni.
Pour into a greased baking dish; top with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Wash, drain, cap and slice strawberries. Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with vanilla wafers. Beat together the margarine, cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Spread creamed mixture over wafers. Top with a layer of sliced berries. Top with a layer of whipped topping.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. (Best to make and serve the same day, but will keep overnight.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream potatoes with sugar, butter and vanilla.
Mix brown sugar, flour and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until tender.
Pull meat from bones and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken.
Blend flour, baking powder, salt and milk until smooth. Spread flour mixture evenly over chicken.
Blend soup and broth over heat and pour over flour mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until brown.

title: baked onions
directions: Slice the onions and saute in butter.
Layer half of the onions in casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Layer remaining onions and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour a little white wine in casserole and bake until golden and tender.

title: taco salad
directions: Top with 8 ounces shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: butter baked chicken and gravy
directions: Dip chicken in 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Roll in mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Melt butter or margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put chicken into pan, skin side down.
Bake in a 425° oven for 30 minutes.

title: squash au gratin
directions: Cut up squash and onion; cook in small amount of water until tender.
Drain squash, but save liquid.
Melt the butter.
Add flour and gradually the milk and liquid from squash.
Cook until sauce is thick.
Add salt, 1/2 cup grated cheese, green pepper and squash.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: helen's pork chops
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan in order given.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for thin chops or 1 1/2 hours for thick chops.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole or black frying pan.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Spoon into 1 pie crust and cover with the other crust.
Crimp edges to seal. Cut slit in top crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: dirt pudding
directions: You will need a flowerpot (washed well), plastic flowers and gummy worms.
Cover hole in bottom of flowerpot with one Oreo.

title: nick's famous shrimp scampi
directions: In a 14-inch skillet, combine 1 stick butter, olive oil and 2 cloves chopped garlic.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add chicken stock; bring to a boil.
Add white wine, stirring constantly.
Add 1/4 cup bread crumbs, mixing well while boiling.
Add shrimp, balance of garlic, basil and butter; squeeze lemon over pan.
Cook, covered, for 5 minutes.
Bring pasta to a boil; drain well. Preheat oven to broil.
Mix pasta in with shrimp scampi.
Cook for 3 minutes; sprinkle balance of bread crumbs over top of frypan. Place in oven for 5 to 10 minutes, or until bread crumbs begin to brown.
Serve with Monticello Pinot Noir.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Cook egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice until thick. Cool.
Whip egg whites; add 3 tablespoons sugar gradually.
Fold into cooled mixture.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into mixture.

title: portuguese rice pudding
directions: Bring water, rice, lemon peel or orange peel and 1 cinnamon stick to a boil. Then add the milk and sugar. Stir frequently. Beat egg yolks in a bowl. When rice is fully cooked, quickly stir in the egg yolk. Remove the orange or lemon peel and the cinnamon stick from mixture. Place pudding in a serving tray and top with sprinkled ground cinnamon.

title: barbara anderson's carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs until creamy. Add dry ingredients and mix carrots and nuts last.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: croutons
directions: Melt margarine; pour over bread cubes.
Mix well.
Add seasoning from Ranch dressing; toss until well mixed.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Cool and store.

title: squash and applesauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange squash upside down in shallow pan.
Bake until almost tender, about 35 minutes.
Turn, cut side up, and add salt to taste.
Brush with margarine.
Sprinkle generously with brown sugar.
Divide applesauce between halves. Return to oven and bake for about 15 minutes.

title: croque monsieur
directions: Butter one side of each piece of bread.
Place one piece, butter side down, in skillet over medium heat.
Place one piece of cheese over bread.
Place ham over cheese and a second piece of bread, butter side up, over all.
Brown bottom piece of bread. Turn entire sandwich and brown other side. Repeat 3 more times to make four sandwiches in all.

title: crescent coffee cake
directions: Pat one can of the rolls into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat egg yolk, cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla together.
Spread on top of the rolls.
Place the other can of rolls on top.
Beat the egg white until stiff; brush on top of the rolls.
Mix together the 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle on for topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and whipped topping.
Add other ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers; remove seeds and white portion. Parboil 5 minutes in boiling water. Melt butter in saucepan and blend with flour and seasonings. Add milk gradually while stirring constantly. Bring to a boil and allow to boil until mixture thickens. Remove from heat. Add flaked salmon and chili sauce. Stuff peppers with this mixture. Cover with buttered bread crumbs. Place in baking pan and add 1/2 cup boiling water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and beans.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well. Spoon into a 2-quart baking dish.
Cook at 350° until bubbly. Add bread crumbs and oleo mixture the last 5 minutes of cooking. Can be frozen.

title: camp stew
directions: Combine first three ingredients with all chicken broth and 1/4 pork broth in large boiler.
Add other ingredients, one at a time. Let mixture come to a boil after each addition.
Thicken with crushed crackers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly; sprinkle spices and mix again thoroughly.
Store in a covered container in your refrigerator.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250°.
Cook until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 pies.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix pickles and onions together.
Heat other ingredients to boiling.
Pour over pickles and onions and let set until cool. Will keep in refrigerator for 1 year.
Can also freeze.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cream together shortening, sugar, milk and vanilla. Add eggs and mix. Then add dry ingredients.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar with berries.
Set oven at 350°.
Put butter in heavy baking dish.
Set in oven to melt.
Stir together 1/2 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Pour this batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Put sugared fruit on top of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and cherry juice.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and blend thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni cheese salad
directions: Combine most ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard and salt; and toss lightly.
Serves 6.

title: inez's coconut cake
directions: Bake cake.
This makes 2 layers.
Let cake cool and split into 4 layers.
Mix powdered sugar, sour cream and coconut together and refrigerate while baking cake.
When cake is cool, spread between layers and on top.
Put in refrigerator for 5 days.

title: nancy's pound cake
directions: Cream butters and
sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, beating after each addition.
Add extracts.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Store in tight tin.
Ages well!

title: snowfall cake
directions: Dissolve the
gelatin
in
the cold water.
Add the hot water, granulated
sugar, pineapple and juice and lemon juice. Blend well and let "set" in refrigerator until slightly thick.

title: country cream caramels
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, place sugar and corn syrup.
Cook mixture slowly, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and syrup reaches boiling stage.
Place candy thermometer in pan. Boil syrup, without stirring, over high heat until thermometer registers 300°.
Remove from heat; quickly add a few butter bits; return to heat.
Boil over high heat, stirring constantly, and gradually add remaining butter.
Add cream slowly while candy continues to boil; stir constantly to prevent burning and sticking.
Boil until thermometer registers 246° to 250°, depending on hardness of candy preferred.
Add vanilla, stirring only enough to blend.
Pour candy into a buttered 8 x 11-inch shallow pan.
Let cool for 4 to 6 hours.
Turn out of pan and cut into squares with a heavy knife.
Wrap in wax paper and store in a tin box with a close-fitting lid.

title: date balls
directions: Boil oleo, salt, sugar, vanilla, dates and eggs together 5 minutes.
Then pour over Special K cereal.
Roll in balls and roll in coconut.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Drain mushrooms, reserve liquid, add enough water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Gradually stir liquid into flour mixture.
Put back to heat.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Add mushrooms.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: southern pea salad
directions: Mix ingredients well, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Chill. Serves 4 to 5.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water, mixing thoroughly.
Add strawberry pie filling.
Mix well.
Let set in refrigerator until congealed.
Then cream the sour cream and cream cheese together. Add the sugar gradually.
Spoon over top of congealed jello mixture.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired.

title: chess cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs well.
Add flour, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes at 325°.
Shut oven off.
Leave cake in for 8 minutes.
Take out; sprinkle with xxx sugar.

title: patience cake
directions: Make cake by directions on box.
Bake in three 9-inch layers. Cool.
Spread the frosting between layers and on top.
Wrap in Saran Wrap; refrigerate.
Very good anytime, but improves after a day or two.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and pour over vegetable mixture.
Let stand overnight.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix and chill sugar and cranberries for 1 hour.
Mix and chill the pineapple and marshmallows for 1 hour.
Mix the mixtures together and add whipping cream or Cool Whip.
Add pecans and chill before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Stir margarine in hot rice until melted.
Mix rice, corn, soup and cheese.
Bake briefly at 350 degrees until cheese melts.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add water and vinegar.
Cook over simmer burner until thick.
Add salt and butter, then diced beets. Reheat.

title: light and easy dessert
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
Smooth top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: loukoumothes
directions: Sift flour with salt and mix with dried yeast. Add water slowly and beat until mixture is smooth. Cover with towel and let it rest for 1 hour.
Heat oil to just under smoking point in deep fryer and drop teaspoons of mixture in, about 6 at a time.
Dip teaspoon in cold water after each drop to prevent sticking. Turn; lift out with a slotted spoon.
Sprinkle with honey and cinnamon.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll into a ball (can divide into 2 rolls).
May be covered with additional nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or French bread.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops, potatoes, carrots, onion and bell pepper in a baking dish.
Pour cream of chicken soup over the meat and vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
You may want to add a little water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok or deep pan.
Add chicken; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add vegetables; fry 1 minute.
Add water; cover and fry 2 minutes.
Stir and fry 2 more minutes.
Add red pepper and soy sauce.
Cook, stirring until chicken and vegetables are coated with sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Serve with buttered garlic bread.

title: bouquet garni
directions: Tie ingredients in cheesecloth or muslin bag.
Add to casseroles, stews, sauces and soups.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and core apples.
Chop coarsely and measure 1 3/4 cups into large bowl.
Add raisins and sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar and syrup in large bowl.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Remove and add peanuts.
Microwave on High 3 minutes. Remove and add butter and vanilla.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes. Remove and stir in soda.
Stir well and pour onto a prepared cookie sheet, greased.
Later, break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate crispy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour mixture.
Stir in Rice Krispies and chocolate morsels.
Drop by level tablespoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheets to cool.

title: danish dumplings
directions: Bring to a boil the milk, butter and salt.
Add the flour all at once; stir until it forms a ball around spoon.
Add 1 beaten egg; beat until smooth.
Add 3 more eggs, one at a time.
Beat until each one is smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls onto boiling soup.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into chunk size (stems and all).
Chop onion.
Slice mushrooms thin.
Cut hard-boiled eggs into wedges. Put all this into a large salad bowl and sprinkle with garlic and seasoned salt.
In a small bowl mix mayonnaise and mustard.
Pour over vegetables and eggs.
Toss.
Scatter olives and nuts over top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil 4 chicken breasts until done.
Cook spaghetti in remaining broth.
Do not drain; let boil down.
Cut up Velveeta in cubes.
Put Ro-Tel in Velveeta; melt together in microwave.
Break up chicken.
Add to spaghetti.
Mix sauce in with spaghetti and chicken.
This is very filling!

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Season with salt and pepper; dredge in corn meal.
Heat bacon drippings in a heavy skillet.
Add tomatoes; fry slowly until browned, turning once.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla and zucchini. Sift dry ingredients and gradually add to mixture; stir in nuts. Grease 2 loaf pans well.
Bake at 325° 50 to 60 minutes.

title: linguine with herbed shrimp
directions: Cook shrimp in 1/4 cup olive oil in a skillet or medium pan with thyme, basil, parsley, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Cook just until shrimp turns pink and slightly firm.
Do not overcook. Remove from pan.
In same pan, heat 1/4 cup olive oil; add garlic and saute briefly.
Add artichoke hearts; saute briefly.
Add tomatoes and cook over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Add the shrimp and olive oil and cook just until shrimp is heated through, but do not overcook!

title: best ever scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes very thin.
Mix soups, onion and ham together. Mix in potatoes.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Boil shrimp with 4 cloves of garlic (unpeeled) for 8 minutes. Peel shrimp; chop some and leave some whole.
Combine all other ingredients together; add shrimp last.
Let stand overnight.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Boil macaroni for 10 minutes.
When done, place in casserole dish.
Cut up one stick of margarine or butter until completely melted in macaroni.
Then add milk, cheese and other ingredients.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: strawberry cake filling
directions: Wash and slice strawberries.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, 7-Up and food coloring until thick.
Cool.
Add cream (strawberries may be cooked in filling).
Layer of filling and layer of Cool Whip between layers.
(Can use frozen strawberries; thaw and drain, whole box.)

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cereal in large bowl.
Melt margarine and peanut butter over low heat.
Pour this over sugar and cereal. Cool, then mix together with hands.
If mixture does not hold together, more melted peanut butter may need to be added.
Form into 1/2 inch balls.
It not firm, chill.

title: heavenly halo mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup syrup.
Dissolve jello and marshmallows in boiling water.
Add reserved syrup.
Chill until almost thickened.
Whip.
Fold in pineapple, whipped cream and cake cubes.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan or 3-quart ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on serving plate.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: boiled apple dumplings
directions: Bring apples, water and brown sugar to a boil and cook until half done.
With hands, mix butter into dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk.
Drop dough on boiling apples.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with milk.
Other fruit can be used instead of apples.

title: chili-fix-in stew
directions: In a large skillet, combine ground beef and 1 package of chili fixin mix.
Cook on medium heat until meat is brown; drain. Pour into a large soup pot; combine other ingredients.
Bring to a boil on medium heat for 1 hour; stir.
Reduce heat to low for approximately 1 hour and simmer.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cut butter into small pieces in a large mixing bowl.
Add oats and pour in boiling water.
Let stand for 20 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in deep dish unbaked pie shell. Bake 30 min. at 350 degrees.

title: spinach, rice & feta pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Melt butter in large saucepan over medium heat. Add onions and saute 3 minutes. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk, stirring with a whisk until well blended. Bring mixture to a boil and cook 1 minute or until slightly thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in rice, feta cheese, egg, egg whites and spinach. Pour mixture into pie shell, coated with cooking spray. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over pie. Bake for 35 minutes or until set. Broil 2 minutes or until pie is golden brown.

title: chicken divine
directions: Grease pan.
Mix chicken and 1/2 cup cheese.
Put mixture in crescent rolls.
Roll up and place in baking dish.
Mix and cook over medium heat 1/2 cup cheese, can of soup and 1 cup milk.
Pour over crescent rolls and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: hash brown quiche(serves 6)
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie plate.
Press thawed hash browns between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Fit into pie plate, cutting and trimming to make a solid crust.
Brush hash browns with melted butter (be sure to brush edges too).

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut batter into mixture.
Add egg to flour mixture and mix well.
Take teaspoon size pieces and press onto pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: groente (oven) soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle or roaster.
Cook in a 325° oven for 4 hours.
Stir about every hour.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Prepare chicken and season with seasoned salt; let drain on paper towel.
Heat oil in electric skillet to 350°.
Oil should fill skillet about 1/2 way.
Dip chicken in flour, then in buttermilk and back in flour.
When chicken browns on one side, turn to other side.
It's best to turn only 1 time.
Drain chicken when done on paper towel.

title: chocolate cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Melt cheese.
Use either the top of a double boiler or melt in a glass bowl in the microwave oven (cook 90 seconds, stir; cook 60 seconds, stir; cook 30 seconds at a time until melted).
Add drained ground beef and chili.
Heat until thoroughly hot.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix butter, vanilla, peanut butter and confectioners sugar. Melt wax in a double boiler. Add chocolate chips. Make peanut butter mixture into balls. Dip into chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed.
Add condensed milk and then fold in Cool Whip.
Blend well.
In large container layer bottom with cookies, bananas and top with pudding.
Repeat 2 or 3 times.

title: maw maw's dumplins
directions: Let stand until cool.
Roll out thin.
Cut in strips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, olives and onions.
Form into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar until blended, cool.
Stir in egg.
Blend flour, baking soda and salt together.
Blend into margarine mixture.
Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut in bars while warm.
Makes 18 bars.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel the eggplant and boil in salted water (slice or cube). When tender, drain and mash.
Soak toasted bread in the light cream.
(I use half and half and you may need a little more than the 1/4 cup.)
Mix with the mashed eggplant and add the eggs, chopped onion, melted butter, salt and pepper.
Mix all together by hand, stirring.
Pour into buttered 10-inch casserole dish.
Add the 2 or 3 tablespoons fresh cream to the top of casserole.
Smooth over the top of the eggplant with the bowl of a tablespoon or use a spatula.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: you-"can"-do-it fig newtons peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in small microwavable bowl. Top with remaining ingredients. Microwave on HIGH 30 seconds. Cool slightly.

title: oriental salad
directions: Brown in a large skillet Ramen noodles, almonds and sesame seed.
Let cool.

title: "fat free" pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Marinate overnight.
Serve chilled.
Makes a large salad.

title: ten yolk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one or two at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with water.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 350° in three 8-inch pans or two 9-inch pans. Frost with Seven Minute Icing.

title: anniversary punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Dilute frozen juices as directed on cans.
Blend juices and cherries. Stir in sugar syrup; chill.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: george washington pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1 can cherries and 1 cup sugar, and pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Then pour over this 1 can of cherries mixed with 1 cup sugar.
Put butter on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve as is or with ice cream.

title: banana fluff
directions: Whip the cream.
Fold in sour cream,
then
add pudding mixture.
Layer
vanilla
wafers, thin sliced bananas, half of pudding mix
and stream of chocolate syrup.
Repeat layers and refrigerate.
Make a day ahead.

title: venison soup
directions: Brown venison in pan. Add onion and cook 5 minutes. Loosen meat from kettle. Add remaining ingredients, except soup.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Add tomato soup and simmer 10 minutes longer. Good with hot bread.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften and cream.
Add onion, chili sauce, mayo and horseradish and mix with mixer.
When all is mixed thoroughly, hand mix whole shrimp.
Chill.

title: crusty pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until it becomes ice cream.
Beat eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, vanilla flavoring and lemon flavoring. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Turn oven temperature down to 200° and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: butterscotch krispie treats
directions: Combine butterscotch pieces and butter in a 2-quart microwavable glass casserole.
Cook, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes at power level 7 or until melted.
Stir in marshmallows.
Cook, uncovered, 3 to 4 1/2 minutes at power level 6 or until marshmallows are softened.
Stir twice.
Blend until smooth.
Stir rice cereal into marshmallow mixture.
Press into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; cool and cut.

title: chicken-swiss and wine casserole
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with cheese. Thin soup with wine.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Mix stuffing with melted butter and sprinkle over top. Bake at 300° for 90 minutes, uncovered.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease muffin tins; fill cups full.
Bake at 375°, 25-30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water 8-10 minutes until just tender.
Drain and slice into 1/4 inch slices.
Toss with onion and green pepper in a large bowl.
Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Boil stewing hen until well done.
Remove from broth and debone.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Wash and separate celery stalk.
Cut diagonally 3/4-inch long.
Wash and cut up onions. Cut and drain bean sprouts, bamboo shoots and water chestnuts. Bring broth to a boil.
Add onions, bean sprouts, bamboo shoots and water chestnuts.
When vegetables are done, add chicken and pimientos.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes more.
Add enough water to dissolve cornstarch.
Add to pot and stir until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and serve over egg noodles.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Remove stem ends from 4 or 5 medium tomatoes.
Cut each tomato in half.
Set oven control to broil.
Dot each half with 1/2 teaspoon margarine or butter.
Sprinkle each half with salt, pepper and basil leaves or oregano.
Broil tomato halves 3-inches from heat for about 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bertha's fudge
directions: Bring first 4 items slowly to a boil in a heavy pan.
Boil and stir for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add almond Hershey bars, marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and chopped pecans.
Beat 5 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
This does not need to be refrigerated.
A family favorite!

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, syrup and margarine for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Take off stove and be ready to stir.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda and stir.
Mixture will change appearance and texture.
Then pour over popped corn.

title: black walnut cake
directions: In large bowl beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix and add to the egg mixture.
Add milk and beat until smooth.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour mixture into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: eggs taos(8 servings)
directions: In large skillet, saute garlic and onion in butter over high heat.
Stir in flour.
Add heated milk and whisk constantly until thick.
Add green chiles, salt and pepper.
Remove sauce from heat and set aside.

title: low calorie tangy chicken
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole and bake at 350° until tender.

title: kielbasa and sauerkraut
directions: Brown onion and small pieces of bacon; drain.
Add drained sauerkraut to onions and bacon.
Add tomato juice, pinch of garlic powder, brown sugar and kielbasa.
Simmer for least 90 minutes.

title: daffodil cake
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and salt. Beat until stiff.
Fold in sugar.
Pour half of egg white mixture into another bowl.
Into one half, fold in vanilla and 1/2 cup flour.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add extracts; fold into remaining egg whites. Fold in remaining flour.
Pour over mixture in tube pan.
Cut through batter several times with knife.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Invert pan and cool.
Remove and frost as desired.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Melt margarine and add brown sugar in large mixing bowl.
Stir until well mixed. Allow to slightly cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add half of ingredients; mix.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Mix. Add nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Spread into greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In plastic bag, combine lemon juice, vegetable oil, garlic and bouillon.
Marinate chicken in this 2 hours or overnight (the longer you marinate the better).
Remove from marinade; grill or broil as you like, basting frequently.
Slice chicken into strips; place on tortillas.
Top with cheese and garnishes.
Fold and eat.

title: strawberry country cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Butter the bottom of two 8 in cake pans. Then line them with parchment paper and butter and flour the lined pans.

title: roast chicken with apple stuffing
directions: Pour 3/4 cup of butter over stuffing.
Mix in large bowl; toss to moisten evenly.
Add apples, celery, raisins, onion, salt, sage and pepper; mix well.
Spoon stuffing into body cavity, packing loosely.
Truss chicken; place in roasting pan.
Brush with remaining 2 tablespoons butter and lemon juice.
Roast in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer inserted into thickest part of thigh not touching bone registers 190°.
Let stand 10 minutes before carving.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Generously grease six 6-ounce custard cups or 8 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in flour, milk and salt just until smooth (do not overbeat).
Fill custard cups about 1/2 full, muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes.
Decrease oven temperature to 350°. Bake custard cups 20 minutes longer, muffin cups 15 minutes longer.
Immediately remove from cups; serve hot.
Makes 6 or 8 popovers.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef with 1 large onion chopped.
Mix spaghetti sauce, cottage cheese and tomatoes.
Layer sauce and noodles.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over each layer.
May use Parmesan cheese in addition to the Mozzarella cheese if desired.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and let melt.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions.
Alternate vegetables in a casserole dish with water chestnuts, mushrooms, onions and cheese.
Pur soup over top and bake in moderate oven until heated.

title: new orleans shrimp
directions: *Flavor is best when shrimp are not peeled.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix and sift the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add almonds and chocolate chips; mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: orange sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add boiling water and cook until clear, stirring constantly.
Place over hot water and continue cooking 5 minutes longer.
Pour over egg yolk and beat well.
When partially cooled, add fruit juices and rinds.
Cool. Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until bubbly, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crumb pie
directions: Mix water, 1 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla until all is dissolved.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Mix flour, lard, sugar, soda and vanilla until crumbly and well mixed. Put on top of pie and bake at 350° until set.

title: crock pot macaroni and cheese
directions: In frying pan, cook some bacon pieces until done, add onion (green onions are good), small slices of carrot, green pepper, scrambled egg, mushrooms, and cook until done.
Do not drain grease.
Add cooked rice and soy sauce to taste.
You can add anything you want to fried rice, such as sausage, but the bacon makes it better.
Also, put the carrots in first, they take longer to cook.
Don't scramble eggs in rice.

title: homemade strawberry cake
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cherry and apple dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dump cherry and apple pie fillings into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Make sure it is even all over.
Dump the cake mix into pan, make sure it is even all over.
Slice the stick of butter and place all over the top.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: vegetable dip for chips
directions: Chill well.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: mocha heath bar cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Mix chocolate wafers with the butter and press into the bottom and up 1/2 of the sides of a 9-inch greased spring-form pan.
Finely chop 4 of the Heath bars, sprinkle over crust and refrigerate crust while preparing filling.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in pie shell.
Place in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn heat down to 325° for 30 minutes.
Custard will bake in 40 minutes.

title: shakedown cake
directions: Combine ingredients, except powdered sugar, and mix to blend. Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes, then shake down.
Bake 10 more minutes; shake down.
Bake 10 more minutes; shake again.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Remove from oven. Cool and cut as brownies.
May sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Cream crisco, egg, brown sugar and molasses. Stir in dry ingredients; chill dough and roll into walnut size balls.
Dip balls in sugar and put on cookie sheet separated.
Sprinkle water on top; Bake 350° 9-12 min.
Still soft when done. don't overbake.

title: light and zesty chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: beef and onion stew
directions: In a large, heavy pot, heat butter.
Add meat and cook until browned on both sides.
Remove meat and set aside.
Add onions to pan and cook until browned.
Stir in flour and sugar and cook until browned.
Stir in consomme and beer.
Bring to boil.

title: mother's pound cake
