directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk and flavoring.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch angel food cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours. This cannot be baked in Bundt pan because it will not hold all the batter.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; squeeze out water.
Mix all ingredients except bread well.
Let set overnight.
Take out center of loaf of bread. Cut into bite-size pieces.
Put dip in center of bread with pieces around.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt in mixing bowl; beat well.
Sift flour and soda together; add to first mixture.
Beat well again.
Add apples and pecans.
This mixture will be very stiff.
You may have to mix it by hand.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.
Do not overcook.

title: date spice cake
directions: Stir together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Toss dates with mixture to separate them; add walnuts.
Beat eggs slightly.
Gradually beat in sugar until thickened and pale lemon color.
Add sour cream and beat to blend.
Gradually and gently beat in flour mixture until batter is smooth. Turn into a greased 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch cake pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet dough for rolls
directions: Bring to a bubble the milk and water; cool in fridge to lukewarm.
Add the remaining ingredients to milk mixture; beat until well mixed.
Sift 7 to 8 cups of flour.
Stir in 5 1/2 to 6 cups until dough starts to thicken, then add remaining 1 to 2 cups until ready for kneading.
Turn onto floured board and knead for 2 to 5 minutes until it becomes smooth and elastic.
Round up in greased bowl, rounded side up.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise in warm place for 2 to 2 1/2 hours (don't rush).
Punch down and let rise again 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: exa's roll recipe
directions: Mix potato water, sweet milk and shortening; let cool until lukewarm.
Add egg, sugar, salt and dissolved yeast, mix well. Add about two cups of flour, beat well until it is the consistency of pan cake mixture.
Cover and keep in a warm place one hour. Add enough flour to kneed into biscuit dough texture.
Let rise until double in bulk about one hour.
If ready to use, pinch off desired amount, roll out, cut with biscuit cutter, dip in melted butter and place close together in baking dish with sides.
Let rise again and bake.
Punch down unused mixture and place in refrigerator.
Mixture will last about two weeks in refrigerator.

title: pineapple banana supreme cake
directions: Bake cake following directions on mix box. Cool completely. Poke holes in cake. Spread pineapple over top using juice and all. Spread pudding on top of pineapple. Slice bananas and place in pudding. Spread Cool Whip and sprinkle crushed walnuts on top.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Line baking pan with foil.
Pour rice on foil and lay chicken on top of rice.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Pour both cans of soup and milk over the chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: sonora chicken
directions: Mix soup, chiles, taco sauce, milk and onion in a bowl.
Then tear tortillas in small pieces.
Now, find a big casserole pan and place chicken on bottom, then half the tortillas, half the sauce and half the cheese on top of chicken.
Repeat this layering, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; pack lightly in a large, greased loaf pan.
Bake in the oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet; pour off excess fat.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Cook in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ground chuck and okra
directions: Cook ground meat with onion; drain grease.
Add tomatoes; simmer 10 minutes uncovered.
Layer okra and cover.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes until okra are tender.
Small amount of parsley, celery and bell peppers may be added with onion if desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.
More okra may be used.

title: grandma's old-fashioned coffee cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Reserve 3/4 cup mixture. To remaining mixture, add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Put into 2 slightly greased cake pans.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup of reserved mixture on top and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Strawberries, orange and lemon slices can be floated in the punch.

title: oven fried squash
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a plastic bag, combine squash and salad dressing; shake well.
Combine crumbs and cheese in another bag.
Add squash; shake well.
Arrange in single layer in shallow pan well sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake, turning once.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together and set aside.
Mix pretzels and butter, press in 9 X 13 inch pan; bake 400 for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread cream cheese mixture over pretzels. Spread whipped topping over mixture and chill.
Dissolve gelatin in hot pineapple juice; add the strawberries and allow to set slightly, pour over top of other layers.
Refrigerate until set. Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: mama ricc's pepperoni snacks
directions: Unroll crescent rolls; cut each piece of dough into three pieces.
Spread pizza sauce on with a barbecue brush.
Add cheese and pepperoni and roll up.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: In 4-quart bowl, layer 1/2 each of spinach, eggs, lettuce, beans, onions and chopped pepper.
Repeat layers.
Spread salad dressing evenly over top.
Cover at least 12 hours.
Garnish.

title: pasta pinwheels
directions: Pour 1/2 sauce into a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Combine spinach, Ricotta, 3/4 cup Mozzarella, Parmesan and egg; mix well. Spread each noodle with scant 1/2 cup mixture; roll up and cut in half crosswise.
Place rolls, cut side down, in dish.
Top with remaining sauce.
Cover; bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and additional Parmesan.
Makes 12 (2-inch) pinwheels.

title: pistachio salad(green stuff)
directions: Stir pudding mix into canned pineapple in a bowl.
Stir in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Add nuts (optional).
Chill well before serving.
Can be served with dinner or as a dessert.
Great for the holidays.

title: date puddin
directions: Top with Cool Whip or cream.

title: granola
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, except raisins, together and spread on 2 cookie sheets.
Warm honey so it will pour in thin stream. Pour honey and oil over dry ingredients.
Toss to coat.
Bake at 225° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove and toss in raisins.
Place in container.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix jello, hot and cold water, sugar and salt; set in refrigerator to chill.
Mix crushed, drained pineapple, diced apples and bananas.
Combine with chilled jello.
Pour into 13 x 9 inch pan.
Cook pineapple juice, flour, sugar and egg until thick; cool.
Follow directions on box for Dream Whip.
Mix Dream Whip with cooked ingredients and cover top of jello; sprinkle with nuts.
Keep covered in refrigerator.

title: chicken wings appetizers
directions: Cut off and discard wing tips; cut each wing in half at joint. Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine 3/4 cup picante sauce, honey, soy sauce, mustard seed, oil, ginger and orange juice in small bowl; mix well. Pour over chicken wings. Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Place wings on foil-lined 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Additional picante sauce may be added. Serve warm.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Grate carrots and
add	raisins, celery and mayonnaise. Blend together.
Garnish with parsley, cherry and sugar coated raisins. (Toss an additional
pound
raisins
in 1 ounce sugar to make sugar coated raisins.) Serves 24.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 stick of oleo in casserole dish.
Mix pineapple, sugar, flour, salt and cheese.
Spread mixture in dish.
Top with crackers mixed with remainder of oleo, melted.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and oleo over low heat. After it's melted, put in Rice Krispies and almost all of powdered sugar. Mix all ingredients by hand and form into 1-inch balls. Melt chocolate. Dip your peanut balls into chocolate and tap off excess. Place on wax paper or foil.
Makes 80 or 90 balls.

title: easy chocolate shakes
directions: Pour milk and pudding in blender container.
Blend good.
Add ice cubes.
Blend thoroughly.
Let stand about 3 minutes to thicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Next, mix yolks and milk.
Then combine the sugar and flour mixture and the yolk and milk mixture. Cook in double boiler, stirring often, until thick.
While mixture is cooking, arrange in a large bowl layers of bananas and vanilla wafers.
Pour mixture over this.
Beat egg whites, pinch of cream of tartar and 3 heaping teaspoonfuls of sugar.
Spread over contents in bowl and brown in oven.

title: apple dip
directions: Cut apples into wedges.
Mix cream cheese with brown sugar in a large bowl.
With a spatula, spread cream cheese mix on plate. Then spread caramel dip over cream cheese.
Dip apples and enjoy.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Press over bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese, flour, chocolate and 1 cup sugar in bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in half and half and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300°.
Bake for 55 minutes longer.
Cool for 10 minutes, remove sides of pan. Spread mixture of sour cream and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla over cooled cheesecake.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: cheesecake tarts
directions: Push a vanilla wafer in miniature tart pan and fill cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place 1 tablespoon of cherry pie filling on top.

title: fruit 'n' bran muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Combine egg and milk; add flour mixture with shortening and mix only enough to dampen flour.
Fold in cereal and raisins.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs, dates, nuts, vanilla and flour mixture.
Place batter in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. While hot, cut in small squares, then roll into balls.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen delicious cookies.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepot.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat to simmer.
Simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Correct seasonings.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Dice apples.
Cut grapes in half.
Add nuts, marshmallows and Miracle Whip.
Cool for at least 2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften the cheeses.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into four balls and roll in diced, chopped dried beef.

title: no name cake("you name it")
directions: This is a heavy wonderful cake. There is enough batter for two cakes. Start with an extra large bowl.

title: french fried onion potato fluff
directions: Peel, quarter and boil 4 medium potatoes until fork tender, drain.
Put the potatoes in a large mixing bowl and mash while hot.
Add cream cheese, onion, eggs and flour.
Beat at medium speed with electric whipper until blended.
Increase to high and beat until fluffy.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes thin and season with salt, pepper and garlic. Dip in flour; shake excess off.
Mix eggs and milk together and beat well.
Place tomatoes in egg mixture, then add to cornmeal; do one at a time doing this process.
Heat oil in a skillet and fry tomatoes until golden brown on both sides.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In a very large, heavy saucepot, over medium heat, in hot oil and margarine, cook onion, carrots, celery and potatoes until they are lightly browned, about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Add water, cabbage, tomatoes with their liquid, spinach and zucchini. Over higher heat, heat to boiling, stirring to break up tomatoes. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 40 minutes or until all vegetables are very tender, stirring occasionally.
Do not overcook.
Stir in beans; cook 15 minutes longer or just until soup is thickened.

title: chicken rolls with pork stuffing
directions: Place chicken between 2 pieces of waxed paper or plastic wrap; pound until 1/4 inch thick, bring careful not to tear chicken. Cook and stir sausage and garlic over medium heat until sausage is brown; drain fat.
Stir breadcrumbs, 1/2 teaspoon salt, savory, pepper and egg into meat mixture.
Place about 1/3 cup meat mixture on each breast half.
Roll up and secure with wooden picks.
Place rolls in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brush rolls with melted butter.
Pour remaining butter over rolls.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook uncovered in 400° oven until done, 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove chicken to warm platter; remove wooden sticks. Keep chicken warm.
Pour liquid from baking dish into 1-quart saucepan.
Stir water into cornstarch; pour into liquid.
Stir in bouillon (dry).
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour gravy over chicken; sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with hot noodles.

title: batter dipped shrimp
directions: Wash, shell and devein shrimp.
Drain shrimp on paper towel. Blend egg and milk together.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add egg-milk mixture to dry ingredients and blend until smooth.
Dip shrimp in batter and fry in just enough heated oil to float shrimp.
Heat oil to 385° before adding shrimp.
Drain golden brown shrimp on paper towels.

title: andrew's favorite pecan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Fold in pecans.
Drop from teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken and vegetables
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Roll chicken in flour mixture and fry in oil until brown.
Add all wet ingredients, vegetables and brown sugar to chicken in pan.
Mix together and simmer 20 to 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Cook pasta and cool.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix well all ingredients, but sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Roll into small balls; roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix eggs and oil.
Add other ingredients.
Mix all together until well blended.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: secret irish creme
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Serve chilled.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: peek-a-boo squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until creamy.
Add sugar, 1 cup at a time.
Add
vanilla, almond flavoring and flour.
Mix well. Grease and
flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 2/3 of batter on the bottom
of
pan.
Spread
cherry
pie
filling
on top of batter, then
spread remaining batter over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: french beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole. Bake, covered, in a 300° oven for 4 hours. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice with blender or food processor until smooth.
Add onion and shrimp.
Set overnight. Serve with crackers, chips or vegetables.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Shape into balls. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour broth over chicken.
Spread soup over chicken and broth.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix melted butter, flour and milk together.
Pour over soup and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown crust forms.

title: farmer fruit cake
directions: Cook apples in syrup; cool.
Mix eggs, butter and sugar.
Mix other ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a Bundt pan until done.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Peel and wash potatoes in cold water; dry with paper towels. Potatoes and onion may be grated by hand (traditional method) or diced and slowly dropped into blender until all potatoes are grated.
Combine grated potatoes and onion in bowl with egg, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Heat 1/4-inch of oil in electric skillet to 400°.
Using a ladle or large spoon, drop potato batter into hot oil (one scoop per pancake).
Fry pancakes until nicely browned on both sides.
Remove from skillet and place on paper towels for a few seconds to drain excess oil.
Serve hot with sour cream or applesauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mom's cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until well mixed, about 1 minute.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine.
Make into tiny balls.
Press flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 350° covered.
Uncover and add mushrooms. Cook 15 additional minutes.

title: honey oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine milk, vegetable oil, egg and honey.
Mix well and set aside.
Mix oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Blend all ingredients together; add nuts.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole. Stir flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over margarine.
Put fruit on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey meat loaf with pesto
directions: In large bowl mix together all ingredients.
Shape into loaf. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Top off with some tomato sauce.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Chop chicken and lay on bottom of pan.
Mix broth and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Add Veg-All on top.

title: layered salad
directions: Use large clear bowl so layers show.
Tear lettuce in pieces and layer in bottom of bowl.
Layer remaining ingredients in order.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar and spread over top of salad ingredients.
Cover salad with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight before using.

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: Cut eggplants in quarters.
Peel and boil until tender.
Remove seeds.
Mash or slice.
Set aside.
Saute garlic in olive oil and oleo.
Add eggplant.
Fry until brown.
Add pepper cheese and Salad Supreme.
Serve warm with crackers or Melba rounds.

title: cream sauce for vegetables
directions: Use about 3 cups cooked or canned vegetables (green peas, carrots, etc.). Heat butter. Stir in flour.
Add milk, stirring until smooth. Cook and stir until mixture is thick. Add salt and pepper, then add vegetables.

title: lemon lush
directions: First Layer:
Use 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: bacon and cheese cornbread
directions: Heat cornmeal and 1 1/4 cups milk over medium heat until thick and dry, stirring frequently, about 3 minutes.
Spoon corn meal mixture into a bowl.
Add remaining milk, butter and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in salt, baking powder and chiles, if used. Stir in cheese and bacon.
Pour into a casserole dish or cake pan. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until cooked through.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saut and brown the ground beef with the onion and green pepper. Add the ketchup, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and a little water. Simmer about 1 hour.

title: grandma's refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in about 1/4 cup lukewarm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let stand about 5 or 10 minutes until puffy.
Then add to warm water.
Melt shortening and add it and sugar to water and then beaten egg.
Add about 3 cups flour and beat hard until smooth.
Add rest of flour and mix through thoroughly.
Turn out and knead well until satiny smooth.
Put in bowl and grease top. Let rise until double, then store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Shape as desired.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Grease tops after taking from oven.

title: rogo
directions: Brown the hamburger and season with onion.
(Skim off grease.) Mix the hamburger, rice and cheese with a little margarine. Cover plate with the lettuce.

Put a mound of meat and rice mixture on it. Cover with more cheese. Add Enchilada Sauce over top. Cover with the radishes, celery, onions, green peppers and tomatoes. Add more sauce, if desired. Serve with corn chips.

title: scripture cake(1 kings 17:13)
directions: Follow Solomon's advise for making (Proverbs 23:14).

title: strawberry bavarian
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water or juice from strawberries.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Prepare Dream Whip.
Add Jell-O and strawberries.
Chill.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles to package directions.
Saute onions and peppers in butter for 3 minutes.
Add beef and cook until no longer pink. Drain.

title: zucchini and yellow squash mixture
directions: Boil together squash, onion and carrot until soft in water. Strain and let cool.
Mix soup and sour cream together; fold in squash mixture.
Melt butter and add to stuffing.
Put 1/2 of stuffing in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put squash mixture on top.
Then put other half of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and blend with Cool Whip.
Alternate graham crackers and pudding (ending with crackers on top).
Then frost with chocolate frosting.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 6 mini loaf pans or 2 bread pans.
Combine sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add oil and mix to blend.
Combine flour, salt, soda and poppy seed.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to sugar and eggs.
Beat in vanilla. Pour equally into pans.
Bake for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: gloria's new orleans red beans
directions: Sort out red beans and wash.
Cover beans with water.
Add onions, garlic, green pepper, celery and wine.
Soak overnight.
In morning, add ham bone and bay leaf and few dashes of Louisiana hot sauce.
Cook until beans are tender.
More water may be added. Cook, simmering uncovered, but watch closely.
Mash a few beans to thicken.
When done, serve over rice and sprinkle with chopped green onions.
Salt and pepper to taste while cooking.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In mixing bowl combine sugar, pumpkin, oil, water and eggs. Beat well.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Gradually add to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins, if desired.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool 10 minutes before moving to wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs well and add all other ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tropical punch slush
directions: Mix ingredients and add enough water for large Tupperware container.
Freeze and keep stirred.

title: cherry-pineapple salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: fantastic dessert
directions: Mix together. Press into long 9 x 13 baking pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: chess cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, beating slightly after each addition.
Gradually add sifted flour and vanilla.
Bake in angel food or tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: laurie's crab imperial
directions: Mix all ingredients together, excluding crab meat.
Lightly toss in crab meat.
Arrange in scallop baking shells.
Top with more mayonnaise.
Garnish with red pimento.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serves 4 large or 8 small portions.

title: pam's chicken
directions: Combine soups and sherry. Pour over the chicken breasts in large casserole. Season with garlic powder. Cover with chopped green onions. Cover heavily with shredded cheese. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake 2-3 hours at 275°. Serve with wild rice.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together the Miracle Whip, milk, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in cabbage.

title: cheese straws
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Let butter come to room temperature. Cream butter and cheese together.
Add salt and cayenne and work in flour.
Cover and chill about 1 hour.
Roll out on lightly floured cloth or board about 1/8 inch thick.
Cut in sticks with a sharp knife or pastry wheel about 1/2 inch wide and 4 inches long. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cinnamon favorites
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix chopped nuts, sugar and cinnamon in small bowl. Roll 1 teaspoon of cookie dough in ball and then in nut mixture. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine flour and sugar; cut in butter until coarse and crumbly (similar to pie crust).
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pralines
directions: Separate each cracker into 4 sections.
Arrange in a pan with edges touching.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Stir in sugar and pecans.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently. Spread mixture evenly over graham crackers.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool on wax paper.
Delicious!

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt chocolate bits with butter in a double boiler; cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Sprinkle coconut on a large piece of wax paper.
Blend the marshmallow mixture with the coconut (with your hands) on three separate pieces of wax paper.
Shape mixture into three separate rolls.
This way is much easier to handle than making one large roll.
Wrap each in the wax paper and chill 24 hours.
Cut into slices when ready to serve.
To hurry this, place rolls on a cookie sheet and put into freezer for 30 minutes or until hard and slice.

title: cold tortellini salad
directions: Boil tortellini until soft (longer than package directions). Drain and chill.
Add rest of ingredients and stir well.
Serve cold.

title: banana blueberry pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix the cream cheese and Dream Whip. Fold in powdered sugar and then pour mixture into pie shells. Push banana slices down into mixture and cover with pie filling. Chill for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ripe tomato chow-chow
directions: In large pot, mix together.
Heat ingredients.
Add vegetables and simmer 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cheese into cubes and put in saucepan with 1/4 cup oleo. Heat over medium heat until melted.
Place vegetables in 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over and mix well.
Melt remaining oleo, stir in cracker crumbs and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jelly fruit slaw
directions: Bring 2 cups of grapefruit juice to a boil.
Pour over gelatin, salt and sugar (use more sugar for less tart flavor). Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining 2 cups of juice.
Chill until gelatin starts to congeal.
Fold in cabbage and olives.
Reserve a few slices for garnish.
Brush bottom and sides of a 5 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan in a pan or 2-quart roll in a pan with mayonnaise.
Spoon in gelatin mixture.
Chill until set.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix altogether and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Chop peppers.
Place in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle cheese over peppers.
Pour seasoned eggs over cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Cut into small slices and serve.

title: baked zucchini delight
directions: Mix liquids.
Add sifted dry foods and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Simple, simple!

title: texas cowboy stew
directions: Melt butter, add meat; brown thoroughly.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper, and garlic.
Add seasonings; stir well.
Add tomatoes, corn, beans and potatoes.
Bring to a boil; stir frequently.
Cover and cook till potatoes are tender.

title: three bean bake
directions: Lightly brown the meat and onion; season with salt.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes; place in casserole.
Cover with cheeses and bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: corine's coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries. Heat juice and cola, then add gelatin. Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add cherries and pineapple. Take half of this mixture and pour into a mold or square baking dish and chill until congealed. Set the other half aside.

When the first half is congealed, mix sour cream, nuts and coconut and spread on top of the congealed mixture. Pour the other half of gelatin mixture on top and chill until congealed well. Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: chickenless chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Mix together all except tortillas and cheese.
Grate both cheeses.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread some of the mixture on bottom.
Put some mixture in a tortilla and then both cheeses.
Roll up and place in pan with seam side down. Continue doing this until you get one layer done.
Add some mixture on top of the first layer and some cheese.
Make another layer.
Put remaining mix on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut butter buckeyes
directions: Mix together the peanut butter, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Form into balls and place on a wax paper covered cookie sheet in the refrigerator until cold.
Melt together in double boiler, the chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Using a toothpick, dip balls in chocolate.
You can make lots and freeze them.

title: gluten free glorious morning muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375F and lightly grease 6 Texas sized muffin cups. Put the raisins in a small bowl and cover them with hot water; set aside to while you assemble the rest of the recipe.

In a large mixing bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking soda, xanthan gum, egg enhancer, spices, and salt. Add the carrots, apple, coconut, nuts, and sunflower seeds. In a separate bowl, beat eggs, molasses, oil, and vanilla together. Add to the flour mixture and stir until evenly combined. Drain the raisins and stir into the batter. Divide the batter among the muffin cups and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from oven, let cool 5 minutes, then turn out of pans to finish cooling.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, cook zucchini and onion in butter until tender (about 10 minutes).
Mix in large bowl, parsley, seasoning, eggs and cheese.
Mix well.
Separate dough and press into 10-inch pie pan, covering bottom and sides.
Spread mustard over crust.
Pour the egg and cheese mixture into crust. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until thickened.

title: yummy corn pudding
directions: Combine corn
and eggs; beat well.
Add milk and melted margarine; mix
together sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add to corn mixture, then
add
vanilla.
Turn
into
1/2 quart greased casserole.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and eggs; mix well.
Add peanut butter, peanuts and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Pour filling into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until set.
Top with chopped peanuts, if desired.

title: vegetable fried rice
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, prepare rice as label directs, but reduce 1/4 cup water.
Meanwhile, thinly slice carrots.
Coarsely slice cabbage.
Dice red pepper and cut green onions into 1-inch pieces.

title: spinach, romaine balsamic vinegar
directions: Combine greens and watermelon. Mix next 4 ingredients and refrigerate. Pour over salad; season with salt and pepper.

title: sandra's homemade kahlua
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer 2 hours the water, sugar and instant coffee. Let cool overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: acorn squash vermont style
directions: Cut the squash in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and pulp. Place cut side down on baking dish with 1/2-inch of water.

title: brenda's sourdough biscuits
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, milk and sourdough starter; mix.
Cover and let stand all day or overnight at room temperature.
Spread 1 cup flour on board.
Pour dough on top.
Sift over 1/2 cup flour, salt, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Knead lightly.
If too sticky, add a little more flour.
Pat or roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out biscuits, then pat both sides with butter or oil.
Place biscuits close together in pan.
Let rise 1/2 hour. Bake in preheated 375° oven about 25 minutes.

title: chipped beef on toast
directions: Melt butter in a hot frying pan.
Cut up beef into strips and fry for about 3 minutes.
Remove beef strips from pan and lay on a plate.
Add 3 tablespoons flour to butter in pan.
Stir until thick.
Add milk and stir well.
Simmer until mixture reaches desired consistency.
Add beef and heat.
Toast bread.
Lay bread on plate and spoon beef and gravy over bread.
Serve hot.

title: danny's and jenni's spinach dressing
directions: Heat over double boiler.
Blend oils and vinegar.
Add sugar, mustard and fennel.
Stir and add bacon drippings.
Blend in lemon juice, parsley and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over spinach leaves.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: peppery peanut butter and coconut sandwiches
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Flatten with a rolling pin.
Mix peanut butter, butter and Tabasco.
Spread this on bread slices and cut each into three strips.
Press coconut into strips.
Roll each to form a pinwheel.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Makes 24.

title: garlic grits casserole
directions: Cook grits as instructed on package.
Cut butter and garlic cheese into cooked grits.
Add milk, eggs, salt, pepper and paprika.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle top with selected grated cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle cheese with a little additional paprika. Makes 6 to 8 generous servings.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix 1st 3 ingredients until well blended. With floured hands (mixture will be sticky), roll teaspoons into 1 1/4-inch diameter balls and place 1/2-inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes at 350° until cookies look dry and tops are cracked.
Be careful not to overbake.
Remove from oven and immediately place a chocolate kiss into center of each, pressing down lightly to flatten cookie.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Remove from sheet.
Store in covered container for up to three weeks.

title: harvest pumpkin pie
directions: Mix eggs and pumpkin together.
Blend Equal, salt, spices and coloring.
Add to pumpkin; mix well.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Portion filling into crusts.
Bake in 375° oven until center is set, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and ground beef. Add vinegar, sugar, catsup, onion and mustard. Mix well. Add the beans. Mix well. Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: canned green beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover with water.
Bring to boil and boil 20 minutes.
Pack in clean hot canning jars and seal.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Cut dates.
Put soda on dates.
Add boiling water; let set until you mix the rest.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain beans and pimentos and mix together with other ingredients.
Mix oil, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over beans. Refrigerate.

title: yogurt pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle.
Grease very lightly.
Beat eggs, shortening, milk and yogurt in bowl.
Add other ingredients and beat just a little.
Spoon onto hot griddle.
When bubbles appear on top, flip pancakes.

title: chicken orange
directions: Combine salt, pepper and flour.
Shake chicken pieces in it. Brown chicken in shortening, then drain.
Combine orange juice, water, brown sugar, oregano and nutmeg.
Pour over chicken. Simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar, water, lemon juice, butter, egg and 1 1/4 teaspoons lemon peel in medium saucepan. Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Put sugar in a large bowl, beat eggs well and add to sugar, add half and half, add vanilla and blend well with a fork after each addition.
Add about half of the milk, blend with electric mixer on low.
Add rest of the milk, except about 1/2 cup; blend.
Pour into freezer bucket.
Use the balance of the milk to "rinse" out the bowl and add to mixture in freezer and stir good.
Freeze according to freezer directions.
Makes 1 gallon.
Best to use 6 quart freezer.
Any type fruit can be added to this basic recipe.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a loaf or Bundt pan.

title: jalapeno cocktail pie
directions: Sprinkle peppers, onion and garlic in a well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Cover with cheese.
Pour eggs over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Cool and cut into 1-inch squares.
Yields 6 dozen 1-inch squares.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Sift together flour, sugar and salt. Add lemon.
Beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Combine with milk.
Stir slowly into dry ingredients.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into well buttered dish.
Set in pan of water.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
